reference: Dump trucks were used to block tube entrances and assistance of 80 police were on hand to direct motorists to detours.
translation: A truck-benne was used to block the entrance to the metro and 80 police officers were on duty to orient the motorists to the detours.

source: On avait annoncé aucun retard lié aux embouteillages sur le boulevard périphérique ; l'autre route de la ville.
reference: There were no heavy traffic delays reported on the beltway, the city's alternate route.
translation: "We had announced no delays on the main thoroughfare; the other route of the city.

source: Le Nigeria avait précédemment annoncé qu'il avait l'intention de rejoindre l'AfCFTA dans la semaine précédant le sommet.
reference: Nigeria previously announced it planned to join the AfCFTA in the week leading up to the summit.
translation: Nigeria had previously announced it would join the AfCFTA in the week before the summit.

source: Le commissaire au commerce et à l'industrie de l'Union africaine, Albert Muchanga, a annoncé l'adhésion du Bénin.
reference: AU trade and industry commissioner Albert Muchanga announced Benin was to join.
translation: The African Union Commission, Albert Muchanga, announced Benin's accession.

source: Le commissaire a dit : « nous ne nous sommes pas encore accordés sur les règles de base, ni sur les concessions tarifaires, mais la perspective envisagée est suffisante pour débuter le commerce d'ici le 1er juillet 2020 ».
reference: The commissioner said, "We haven't yet agreed on rules of origin and tariff con[c]essions, but the framework we have is enough to start trading on July 1, 2020".
translation: The Commissioner said, "We haven't yet agreed on the basic rules and tariffs, but the prospect of starting trade in early July 2020 is sufficient to begin the business."

source: La station a maintenu son attitude, malgré la perte d'un gyroscope plus tôt au cours de la mission de la station spatiale, jusqu'à la fin de la sortie spatiale.
reference: The station maintained its attitude, despite the loss of a gyroscope earlier in the space station mission, until the end of the spacewalk.
translation: The station maintained its attitude, despite the loss of a gyroscope earlier in the mission, until the end of the space mission.

source: Chiao et Shaipov ont déclaré avoir observé une distance de sécurité par rapport aux propulseurs de contrôle d'attitude.
reference: Chiao and Sharipov reported being a safe distance from the attitude adjustment thrusters.
translation: Chiao and Shaipov have said they observed a distance of safety from the attitude control propellers.

source: La tour de contrôle russe a activé les jets, ce qui a permis à la station de retrouver une attitude normale.
reference: Russian ground control activated the jets and normal attitude of the station was regained.
translation: The Russian control tower activated the jets, which allowed the station to return to normal attitude.

source: L'affaire a été jugée en Virginie puisque c'est le domicile du fournisseur d'accès à Internet AOL, la société à l'origine des accusations.
reference: The case was prosecuted in Virginia because it is the home to the leading internet service provider AOL, the company who instigated the charges.
translation: The case was settled in Virginia, since the company that made the accusations is the owner of AOL, the company that made the charges.

source: C'est la première fois qu'une condamnation est obtenue grâce à la législation promulguée en 2003 pour lutter contre l'envoi de courriers électroniques de masse, ou spam, provenant de la distribution non sollicitée dans les messageries des utilisateurs.
reference: This is the first time a conviction has been gained using the legislation enacted in 2003 to curb bulk e-mail, aka spam, from unsolicited distribution into users mailboxes.
translation: This is the first time that a conviction has been made in the case of a mass email spammer, or spammer, who has been found guilty of sending bulk email from the distribution of unpaid mail to the users.

source: Jesus, 21 ans, a rejoint Manchester City l’année dernière en janvier 2017, en provenance du club brésilien Palmeiras, pour un montant annoncé de 27 millions de livres sterling.
reference: 21-year-old Jesus joined Manchester City last year in January 2017 from Brazilian club Palmeiras for a reported fee of £27 million.
translation: Jesus, 21, joined Manchester City in January 2017, from Brazilian club Palmeiras, for a reported fee of 27 million pounds.

source: Depuis lors, le Brésilien a disputé 53 matches pour le club toutes compétitions confondues et a marqué 24 buts.
reference: Since then, the Brazilian has featured in 53 matches for the club in all competitions and has scored 24 goals.
translation: Since then, Brazil has played 53 matches for the club all competitions, and has scored 24 goals.

source: Par ailleurs, le docteur Lee s'est dit préoccupé par les signalements d'enfants turcs qui auraient été infectés par le virus de la grippe aviaire A(H5N1) sans pour autant être malades.
reference: Dr. Lee also expressed his concern about reports that children in Turkey have now become infected with the A(H5N1) avian influenza virus without becoming ill.
translation: In addition, Dr Lee said he was concerned about reports of children infected with the bird flu virus A(H5N1) without being ill.

source: Certaines études suggèrent que la maladie doit devenir moins mortelle avant de pouvoir provoquer une épidémie mondiale, a-t-il noté.
reference: Some studies suggest that the disease must become less lethal before it can cause a global epidemic, he noted.
translation: Some studies suggest that the disease should become less deadly before it can cause a global epidemic, he said.

source: On craint que les patients puissent continuer à infecter davantage de personnes en vaquant à leurs occupations quotidiennes si les symptômes de la grippe restent légers.
reference: There is concern that patients may continue to infect more people by going through their daily routines if the flu symptoms remain mild.
translation: We are concerned that patients may continue to infect more people if the symptoms of the flu remain mild.

source: Leslie Aun, porte-parole de la Fondation Komen, a déclaré que l'organisation a adopté une nouvelle règle qui ne permet pas d'accorder de subventions ou de financements aux organisations qui font l'objet d'une enquête judiciaire.
reference: Leslie Aun, a spokesperson for the Komen Foundation, said the organization adopted a new rule that does not allow grants or funding to be awarded to organizations that are under legal investigation.
translation: Leslie Aun, the Komen Foundation's spokesman, said that the organization has adopted a new rule that does not allow grants or funding to be awarded to organizations that are investigated by a judge.

source: La politique de Komen a disqualifié le Planning familial en raison d'une enquête en cours sur la manière dont le Planning familial dépense et déclare son argent, enquête menée par le député Cliff Stearns.
reference: Komen's policy disqualified Planned Parenthood due to a pending investigation on how Planned Parenthood spends and reports its money that is being conducted by Representative Cliff Stearns.
translation: The policy of Komen has disqualified the Planning familial in light of a pending investigation into how the Planning familial uses and discloses its funds, a probe conducted by the House of Representatives member Cliff Stearns.

source: En sa qualité de président de la sous-commission de surveillance et d'enquête, qui relève de la commission de l'énergie et du commerce de la Chambre des représentants, M. Stearns cherche à savoir si les impôts servent à financer les avortements par le biais de la planification familiale.
reference: Stearns is investigating whether taxes are used to fund abortions through Planned Parenthood in his role as chairman of the Oversight and Investigations Subcommittee, which is under the umbrella of the House Energy and Commerce Committee.
translation: Mr. Stearns is seeking to know if the taxpayer funds the abortion by the use of the family planning program.

source: L'ancien gouverneur du Massachusetts, Mitt Romney, a remporté les élections primaires présidentielles du Parti républicain de Floride mardi avec plus de 46 % des voix.
reference: Former Massachusetts governor Mitt Romney won the Florida Republican Party presidential primary election on Tuesday with over 46 percent of the vote.
translation: The former governor of Massachusetts, Mitt Romney, has won the Republican primary election in Florida with more than 46 percent of the vote.

source: L'ancien président de la Chambre des représentants des États-Unis, Newt Gingrich, est arrivé en deuxième position avec 32 %.
reference: Former U.S. Speaker of the House Newt Gingrich came in second with 32 percent.
translation: The former U.S. House of Representatives Speaker of the House of Representatives, Newt Gingrich, is in second place with 32 percent.

source: En tant qu'état où le vainqueur remporte tout, la Floride a décerné à Romney ses cinquante délégués, le poussant ainsi en tête de liste pour la nomination du parti républicain.
reference: As a winner-takes-all state, Florida awarded all fifty of its delegates to Romney, pushing him ahead as the front-runner for the Republican Party nomination.
translation: In the state where the winner wins everything, Florida has given Romney his fifty delegates, which has pushed him into the race for the Republican nomination.

source: Les organisateurs de la manifestation ont affirmé qu'environ 100 000 personnes se sont présentées dans plusieurs villes allemandes telles que Berlin, Cologne, Hambourg et Hanovre.
reference: Organisers of the protest said about 100,000 people turned up in German cities such as Berlin, Cologne, Hamburg, and Hanover.
translation: The organizers of the demonstration said that at least 100,000 people were attending in several German cities such as Berlin, Cologne, Hamburg and Hannover.

source: À Berlin, la police estime qu'il y avait environ 6 500 manifestants.
reference: In Berlin, police estimated 6,500 protestors.
translation: In Berlin, the police estimate there were 6,500 protesters.

source: Des manifestations ont également eu lieu à Paris, Sofia en Bulgarie, Vilnius en Lituanie, La Valette à Malte, Tallinn en Estonie, et Édimbourg et Glasgow en Écosse.
reference: Protests also took place in Paris, Sofia in Bulgaria, Vilnius in Lithuania, Valetta in Malta, Tallinn in Estonia, and Edinburgh and Glasgow in Scotland.
translation: Protests also took place in Paris, Sofia in Bulgaria, Vilnius in Lithuania, La Valette in Malta, Tallinn in Estonia, and Edimburg and Glasgow in Scotland.

source: À Londres, environ 200 personnes ont manifesté devant les bureaux de certains grands détenteurs de droits d’auteur.
reference: In London, about 200 people protested outside some major copyright holders' offices.
translation: At London, about 200 people have protested in front of some of the world's biggest copyright owners.

source: Le mois dernier, il y a eu de grandes manifestations en Pologne lorsque le pays a signé l'ACTA, ce qui a décidé le gouvernement polonais à ne pas ratifier l'accord pour l'instant.
reference: Last month, there were major protests in Poland when that country signed ACTA, which has led to the Polish government deciding not to ratify the agreement, for now.
translation: Last month, there were major protests in Poland when the country signed ACTA, which has forced the Polish government to not ratify the agreement yet.

source: La Lettonie et la Slovaquie ont toutes deux retardé le processus d'adhésion à l'ACTA.
reference: Latvia and Slovakia have both delayed the process of joining ACTA.
translation: Latvia and Slovakia both delayed the process of joining ACTA.

source: Animal Liberation et la Royal Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals (RSPCA) demandent à nouveau l’installation obligatoire de caméras de surveillance dans tous les abattoirs australiens.
reference: Animal Liberation and the Royal Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals (RSPCA) are again calling for the mandatory installation of CCTV cameras in all Australian abattoirs.
translation: Animal Liberation and the Royal Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals (RSPCA) are again calling for the installation of cameras in all slaughterhouses in Australia.

source: L’inspecteur de chef de RSPCA New South Wales David O’Shannessy déclara à ABC que la surveillance et l’inspection des abattoirs devrait être une évidence en Australie.
reference: RSPCA New South Wales chief inspector David O'Shannessy told the ABC that surveillance and inspections of abattoirs should be commonplace in Australia.
translation: The RSPCA inspector in New South Wales, David O'Shannessy, said in ABC that surveillance and inspection of abattoirs should be a must in Australia.

source: « La vidéo-surveillance enverrait à coup sûr un message fort aux personnes travaillant avec des animaux que leur bien-être est de la plus haute importance »
reference: "The CCTV would certainly send a strong signal to those people working with animals that their welfare is of the highest priority."
translation: "The video-surveillance would certainly send a strong message to those working with animals that their welfare is of the highest priority."

source: Selon les données de la carte internationale des tremblements de terre de l’Institut d'études géologiques des États-Unis, aucun tremblement de terre n’a eu lieu en Islande au cours de la semaine précédente.
reference: The United States Geological Survey international earthquake map showed no earthquakes in Iceland in the week prior.
translation: According to the International Geological Survey's Earthquake Map, no earthquake has occurred in Iceland in the past week.

source: Par ailleurs, selon le bureau météorologique islandais, la région de Hekla n’a pas connu de tremblement de terre au cours des dernières 48 heures.
reference: The Icelandic Meteorological Office also reported no earthquake activity in the Hekla area in the past 48 hours.
translation: In addition, the island's meteorological office says Hekla has not experienced any earthquake in the last 48 hours.

source: L'important tremblement de terre ayant entraîné le changement de phase a eu lieu le 10 mars sur la face nord-est de la caldeira du sommet du volcan.
reference: The significant earthquake activity resulting in the phase change had took place on March 10 on the northeast side of the volcano's summit caldera.
translation: The earthquake that caused the change of phase in the summit of the volcano occurred on March 10 on the northeast side of the caldera.

source: Des nuages sombres sans rapport avec une quelconque activité volcanique ont été signalés à la base de la montagne.
reference: Dark clouds unrelated to any volcanic activity were reported at the base of the mountain.
translation: Dark clouds without any connection with any volcanic activity have been reported at the base of the mountain.

source: Les nuages présentaient un risque de confusion quant à savoir si une véritable éruption avait eu lieu.
reference: The clouds presented the potential for confusion as to whether an actual eruption had taken place.
translation: The clouds presented a potential confusion as to whether a real eruption had taken place.

source: Le Luno avait 120–160 mètres cubes de carburant à bord lorsqu’il est tombé en panne, alors que les vents violents et les vagues l’ont poussé dans le brise-lames.
reference: The Luno had 120–160 cubic metres of fuel aboard when it broke down and high winds and waves pushed it into the breakwater.
translation: The Luno had 120–160 cubic metres of fuel aboard when it crashed, while the wind and waves pushed it into the propeller.

source: Des hélicoptères ont secouru les douze membres d'équipage et la seule blessure déplorée était un nez cassé.
reference: Helicopters rescued the twelve crewmembers and the only injury was a broken nose.
translation: The crew of the helicopter was rescued and the only injury was a broken nose.

source: La navire de 100 mètres était en chemin pour récupérer sa cargaison d'engrais habituelle, et les autorités redoutaient initialement qu'il ne déverse son carburant dans la mer.
reference: The 100-metre ship was en route to pick up its usual fertiliser cargo and initially officials feared the vessel could spill a load.
translation: The 100-metre ship was on her way to load her usual fertilizer, and authorities feared initially that it would spill its fuel into the sea.

source: L'amendement proposé a déjà été adopté par les deux chambres en 2011.
reference: The proposed amendment already passed both houses in 2011.
translation: The proposed amendment was already adopted by the two houses in 2011.

source: Un changement a été apporté au cours de cette session législative lorsque la deuxième proposition a d'abord été supprimée par la Chambre des représentants, puis adoptée lundi par le Sénat sous une forme similaire.
reference: A change was made this legislative session when the second sentence was deleted first by the House of Representatives and then was passed in a similar form by the Senate Monday.
translation: A change was made to this session of the legislative session when the second proposal was first removed by the House of Representatives, and then adopted Monday by the Senate under a similar form.

source: La défaillance de la deuxième phrase, qui propose d'interdire les unions civiles entre personnes de même sexe, pourrait éventuellement ouvrir la porte à des unions civiles à l'avenir.
reference: The failure of the second sentence, which proposes to ban same-sex civil unions, could possibly open the door for civil unions in the future.
translation: The second sentence of the text, which proposes to ban same-sex unions, may in fact open the door to civil unions in the future.

source: Suite à ce processus, la HJR-3 sera réexaminée par le prochain corps législatif élu en 2015 ou 2016 pour rester en instance.
reference: Following the process, HJR-3 will be reviewed again by the next elected legislature in either 2015 or 2016 to remain in process.
translation: Following this process, the HJR-3 will be reviewed by the next elected legislature in 2015 or 2016 to remain in the process.

source: Parmi les réalisations de Vautier en dehors de la mise en scène, on peut citer une grève de la faim en 1973 contre ce qu’il considérait comme de la censure politique.
reference: Vautier's achievements outside of directing include a hunger strike in 1973 against what he viewed as political censorship.
translation: Among Vautier's achievements outside the stage, there is a hunger strike in 1973 against what he considered to be political censorship.

source: La loi française a été modifiée. Son militantisme remonte à l’âge de 15 ans, lorsqu’il a rejoint la Résistance française pendant la Seconde Guerre mondiale.
reference: French law was changed. His activism went back to age 15 when he joined the French Resistance during World War II.
translation: The French law has been amended. His militantism dates back to the age of 15 when he joined the Resistance during World War II.

source: Il a fait des recherches dans un livre paru en 1998.
reference: He documented himself in a 1998 book.
translation: He searched for a book published in 1998.

source: Dans les années 60, il est retourné en Algérie, récemment indépendante, pour enseigner la réalisation de films.
reference: In the 1960s he headed back to newly-independent Algeria to teach film directing.
translation: In the 1960s, he returned to Algeria, recently independent, to teach filmmaking.

source: Le judoka japonais Hitoshi Saito, vainqueur de deux médailles d'or olympiques, est mort à l'âge de 54 ans.
reference: Japanese judoka Hitoshi Saito, winner of two Olympic gold medals, has died at the age of 54.
translation: The Japanese judoka Hitoshi Saito, who won two Olympic gold medals, died at the age of 54.

source: La cause du décès a été annoncée comme étant un cancer du canal cholédoque intrahépatique.
reference: The cause of death was announced as intrahepatic bile duct cancer.
translation: The cause of death was announced as a primary bile duct cancer.

source: Il est mort à Osaka mardi.
reference: He died in Osaka on Tuesday.
translation: He died in Osaka yesterday.

source: En plus d'avoir été Champion Olympique et Champion du Monde, Saito était président de la Fédération Japonaise de Judo lors de son décès
reference: As well as a former Olympic and World champion, Saito was the All Japan Judo Federation training committee chairman at the time of his death.
translation: He was also a member of the Japanese Olympic and World Judo Federation during his death.

source: Au moins 100 personnes avaient assisté à la fête, afin de célébrer le premier anniversaire d'un couple dont le mariage s'est tenu l'an passé.
reference: At least 100 people had attended the party, in order to celebrate the first anniversary of a couple whose wedding was held last year.
translation: At least 100 people attended the party, to celebrate the first anniversary of a couple whose marriage last year was celebrated.

source: Les autorité ont déclaré qu'une cérémonie anniversaire officielle avait été prévue à une date ultérieure.
reference: A formal anniversary event was scheduled for a later date, officials said.
translation: The authorities said that a formal anniversary ceremony was scheduled for a later date.

source: Le couple s'était marié au Texas il y a un an et était venu à Buffalo pour fêter l'occasion avec des amis et des parents.
reference: The couple had married in Texas one year ago and came to Buffalo to celebrate with friends and relatives.
translation: The couple had married in Texas a year ago and came to Buffalo for the occasion with friends and family.

source: Le mari, âgé de 30 ans et natif de Buffalo, faisait partie des quatre victimes de la tuerie, mais sa femme n'a pas été blessée.
reference: The 30-year-old husband, who was born in Buffalo, was one of the four killed in the shooting, but his wife was not hurt.
translation: The man, aged 30, was from Buffalo, and was one of the four victims of the shooting, but his wife was not injured.

source: Célèbre mais pas moins controversé tuteur d'anglais ayant enseigné à Modern Education et à King's Glory, Karno a affirmé avoir dirigé 9 000 étudiants au plus fort de sa carrière.
reference: Karno is a well-known but controversial English tutor who taught under Modern Education and King's Glory who claimed to have 9,000 students at the peak of his career.
translation: Karno, a well-known but not less controversial tutor of English, has said he taught 9,000 students at the peak of his career.

source: Dans ses notes, il a utilisé des mots que certains parents considèrent comme grossiers, et il aurait utilisé des jurons en classe.
reference: In his notes he used words which some parents considered coarse, and he reportedly used profanity in class.
translation: In his notes, he used words that some parents consider rude, and he used punctuation marks in class.

source: Modern Education l'a accusé d'avoir imprimé sans autorisation de grandes annonces sur les bus, et d'avoir prétendu être le tuteur principal d'anglais.
reference: Modern Education accused him of printing large advertisements on buses without authorisation and lying by saying that he was the chief English tutor.
translation: Modern Education accused him of printing large advertisements on buses without permission and pretending to be the bus principal.

source: Il a également été accusé précédemment de violation du droit d'auteur, mais n'a pas été inculpé.
reference: He has also been accused previously of copyright infringement, but was not charged.
translation: He also has been accused of copyright infringement, but has not been charged.

source: Un ancien étudiant a affirmé qu’il « utilisait de l’argot en classe, enseignait les techniques de drague dans des écrits, et se comportait comme l’ami des étudiants ».
reference: A former student said that he 'used slang in class, taught dating skills in notes, and was just like the students' friend.'
translation: A former student said he used "argot in class, taught drills in class, and was like the friend of students".

source: Au cours des trois dernières décennies, bien qu’elle soit officiellement restée un État communiste, la Chine a développé une économie de marché.
reference: During the last three decades, despite officially remaining a communist state, China has developed a market economy.
translation: During the last three decades, despite officially remaining a communist state, China has developed a market economy.

source: Les premières réformes économiques ont été réalisées sous la direction de Deng Xiaoping.
reference: The first economic reforms were made under the leadership of Deng Xiaoping.
translation: The first economic reforms were carried out under the direction of Deng Xiaoping.

source: Depuis, la taille économique de la Chine a été multipliée par 90.
reference: Since then, China's economic size has grown by 90 times.
translation: Since then, the size of the Chinese economy has been multiplied by 90.

source: Pour la première fois, l'année dernière, la Chine a exporté plus de voitures que l'Allemagne et a dépassé les États-Unis en tant que plus grand marché pour cette industrie.
reference: For the first time, last year China exported more cars than Germany and surpassed the United States as the biggest market for this industry.
translation: For the first time in a year, the Chinese exported more cars than Germany and surpassed the United States as the largest market for this industry.

source: Le PIB de la Chine pourrait dépasser celui des États-Unis au cours des deux décennies à venir.
reference: China's GDP could be larger than the United States within two decades.
translation: The GDP of China could surpass the US in the two decades to come.

source: La tempête tropicale Danielle, quatrième tempête nommée de la saison des ouragans atlantiques 2010, s'est formée dans l'est de l'océan Atlantique.
reference: Tropical Storm Danielle, fourth named storm of the 2010 Atlantic hurricane season, has formed in the eastern Atlantic Ocean.
translation: The storm Danielle, named the fourth named storm of the 2010 Atlantic hurricane season, formed in the Atlantic Ocean.

source: La vitesse maximale des vents soutenus de cette tempête, qui se produit à environ 4 800 km de Miami, en Floride, atteint 64 km/h.
reference: The storm, located approximately 3,000 miles from Miami, Florida, has maximum sustained winds of 40 mph (64 kph).
translation: The maximum sustained winds of this storm, which is about 4,800 km from Miami, Florida, reach 64 km/h.

source: Les scientifiques du Centre national des ouragans prévoient que Danielle se transformera en ouragan d’ici mercredi.
reference: Scientists at the National Hurricane Center predict that Danielle will strengthen to a hurricane by Wednesday.
translation: The National Hurricane Center expects Danielle to transform into a hurricane on Wednesday.

source: Comme la tempête est loin d'atteindre les côtes, il reste difficile d'évaluer son impact potentiel sur les États-Unis ou les Caraïbes.
reference: As the storm is far from landfall, it remains difficult to assess potential impact to the United States or Caribbean.
translation: As far as the storm is concerned, it is difficult to assess its potential impact on the United States or the Caribbean.

source: Né à Zagreb, la capitale croate, Bobek s'est fait connaître en jouant pour le Partizan Belgrade.
reference: Born in the Croatian capital, Zagreb, Bobek gained fame while playing for Partizan Belgrade.
translation: Bobek was born in Zagreb, capital of Croatia, and has played for Partizan Belgrade.

source: Il le rejoint en 1945 et y reste jusqu'en 1958.
reference: He joined them in 1945 and stayed until 1958.
translation: He joined France in 1945 and stayed there until 1958.

source: Au cours de son passage au sein de l'équipe, il a marqué 403 buts en l'espace de 468 rencontres.
reference: During his time with the team, he scored 403 goals in 468 appearances.
translation: During his time at the club, he made 403 goals in 468 matches.

source: Aucun autre joueur n'a jamais fait plus d'apparitions ou marqué plus de buts pour le club que Bobek.
reference: No one else has ever made more appearances or scored more goals for the club than Bobek.
translation: Bobek has never made more appearances or scored more goals for the club than Bobek.

source: En 1995, il fut élu meilleur joueur de l'histoire du Partizan.
reference: In 1995 he was voted the best player in Partizan's history.
translation: In 1995, he was voted the best player in history of Partizan.

source: Les festivités ont débuté par un spectacle spécial du groupe de renommée mondiale Cirque du Soleil.
reference: The celebrations started with a special show by the world-renowned group Cirque du Soleil.
translation: The festivities started with a special show by the world's biggest group of stars, the Cirque du Soleil.

source: Ont suivi l'Istanbul State Symphony Orchestra, un groupe janissaire, puis les chanteurs Fatih Erkoç et Müslüm Gürses.
reference: It was followed by the Istanbul State Symphony Orchestra, a Janissary band, and the singers Fatih Erkoç and Müslüm Gürses.
translation: They followed the Istanbul State Symphony Orchestra, a janissary band, and the singers Fatih Erkoç and Müslüm Gürses.

source: Puis les derviches tourneurs sont montés sur scène.
reference: Then Whirling Dervishes took to the stage.
translation: Then the derviches turned came on stage.

source: La diva turque Sezen Aksu s'est produite avec le ténor italien Alessandro Safina et la chanteuse grecque Haris Alexiou.
reference: Turkish diva Sezen Aksu performed with the Italian tenor Alessandro Safina and Greek singer Haris Alexiou.
translation: Turkish diva Sezen Aksu performed with Italian tenor Alessandro Safina and Greek soprano Haris Alexiou.

source: Pour terminer, le groupe de danse turc Fire of Anatolia a présenté le spectacle « Troy ».
reference: To finish, Turkish dance group Fire of Anatolia performed the show "Troy".
translation: The group of dancers in Turkey Fire of Anatolia performed the show "Troy".

source: Peter Lenz, un pilote de moto de 13 ans, est mort après avoir été impliqué dans un accident sur l'Indianapolis Motor Speedway.
reference: Peter Lenz, a 13-year-old motorcycle racer, has died after being involved in a crash at the Indianapolis Motor Speedway.
translation: Peter Lenz, a 13-year-old motorcyclist, died after being involved in an accident on the Indianapolis Motor Speedway.

source: Pendant le tour d'échauffement, Lenz est tombé de sa moto, puis a été heurté par son compagnon de course Xavier Zayat.
reference: While on his warm-up lap, Lenz fell off his bike, and was then struck by fellow racer Xavier Zayat.
translation: During the warm-up race, Lenz fell from his motorcycle and was hit by his fellow racer Xavier Zayat.

source: Il a été immédiatement pris en charge par le personnel médical sur la piste et transporté dans un hôpital local où il est mort par la suite.
reference: He was immediately attended to by the on-track medical staff and transported to a local hospital where he later died.
translation: He was immediately transported to a local hospital where he died.

source: Zayat est sorti indemne de l'accident.
reference: Zayat was unhurt in the accident.
translation: Zayat was unhurt in the accident.

source: "En ce qui concerne la situation financière mondiale, Zapatero a poursuivi en disant que ""le système financier fait partie de l’économie, un élément essentiel."
reference: Regarding the global financial situation, Zapatero continued by saying that "the financial system is a part of the economy, a crucial part.
translation: In his speech on the global financial situation, Zapatero continued to say that ""the financial system is part of the economy, a crucial part."

source: Nous traversons une crise financière d'un an, qui a connu son moment le plus aigu au cours des deux derniers mois, et je pense que maintenant les marchés financiers commencent à se redresser. »
reference: We have a year-long financial crisis, which has had its most acute moment in the past two months, and I think now the financial markets are beginning to recover."
translation: "We are currently in a financial crisis of one year, which has experienced its most acute moment in the two last months, and I think that the markets are beginning to recover."

source: La semaine passée, Naked News a annoncé son intention d'augmenter sérieusement le nombre d'heures dédiées au journal en langue internationale, avec trois nouveaux programmes à la clé.
reference: Last week, Naked News announced that it would dramatically increase its international language mandate to news reporting, with three new broadcasts.
translation: The week before, Naked News announced that it would increase the number of hours dedicated to the international news in the language of the week, with three new programs to be announced.

source: Déjà présente en anglais et en japonais, l’organisation mondiale lance des programmes en espagnol, en italien et en coréen, pour la télévision, le web et les appareils mobiles.
reference: Already reporting in English and Japanese, the global organization is launching Spanish, Italian, and Korean-language programs, for television, the web, and mobile devices.
translation: already present in English and Japanese, the global organization launches programs in Spanish, Italian and Korean, for television, the web and mobile devices.

source: Par chance, il ne m'est rien arrivé, mais j'ai assisté à une scène macabre, où des gens essayaient de briser des vitres afin de sortir.
reference: "Luckily nothing happened to me, but I saw a macabre scene, as people tried to break windows in order to get out.
translation: Luckily, nothing happened to me, but I saw a horrific scene where people tried to break windows to get out.

source: Les gens frappaient les vitres avec des chaises, mais les fenêtres étaient incassables.
reference: People were hitting the panes with chairs, but the windows were unbreakable.
translation: People were hitting the windows with chairs, but the windows were broken.

source: « Une des vitres s'est finalement brisée, et ils ont commencé à sortir par la fenêtre », a déclaré Franciszek Kowal, un survivant.
reference: One of the panes finally broke, and they started to get out by the window," said survivor Franciszek Kowal.
translation: "Another window broke, and they started to get out by the window." said Franciszek Kowal, a survivor.

source: Les corps stellaires dégagent lumière et chaleur à cause de l'énergie créée lorsque les atomes d'hydrogène fusionnent (ou se condensent) pour créer des éléments plus lourds.
reference: Stars give off light and heat because of the energy made when hydrogen atoms are merged (or fused) together to form heavier elements.
translation: Stars emit light and heat because of the energy created when hydrogen atoms fuse (or condens) to form more heavy elements.

source: Les scientifiques travaillent à la création d'un réacteur qui peut produire de l'énergie de la même manière.
reference: Scientists are working to create a reactor that can make energy in the same way.
translation: Scientists are working on the creation of a reactor that can produce the same amount of energy.

source: Ceci, cependant, est un problème très difficile à résoudre et il faudra de nombreuses années avant de voir construire des réacteurs à fusion fructueux.
reference: This, however, is a very hard problem to solve and will take many years before we see useful fusion reactors built.
translation: This, however, is a very difficult problem to solve and it will take many years before we see fusion reactors built.

source: L'aiguille en acier reste immergée à cause de la tension à la surface.
reference: The steel needle floats on top of the water because of surface tension.
translation: The steel needle remains submerged because of the tension on the surface.

source: La tension de la surface se crée parce que le magnétisme entre les molécules d'eau à la surface est tellement plus fort qu'avec les molécules d'air au dessus d'elles.
reference: Surface tension happens because the water molecules at the surface of the water are strongly attracted to each other more than they are to the air molecules above them.
translation: The surface tension arises because the surface tension between the water molecules at the surface is so strong that the air molecules above them are so weak.

source: Les molécules d'eau forment une pellicule invisible à la surface qui permet à des objets comme l'aiguille de flotter sur l'eau.
reference: The water molecules make an invisible skin on the water’s surface that allows things like the needle to float on top of the water.
translation: The water molecules form a layer invisible to the surface that allows objects like a needle to float on the water.

source: La lame d'un patin à glace moderne est dotée de deux extrémités avec un creux concave situé entre les deux. Ces deux extrémités permettent une meilleure adhérence à la glace, même lorsqu'elles sont inclinées.
reference: The blade on a modern ice skate has a double edge with a concave hollow between them. The two edges allow for a better grasp of the ice, even when tilted.
translation: A modern ice skate has two ends with concave ends on the two ends. These two ends allow a better grip on ice, even when they are tilted.

source: Comme le bas de la lame est légèrement incurvé, lorsque la lame s'incline d'un côté ou de l'autre, le bord qui est en contact avec la glace s'incurve également.
reference: Because the bottom of the blade is slightly curved, as the blade tilts to one side or the other, the edge which is in contact with the ice also curves.
translation: As the bottom of the blade is slightly curved, when the blade inclines one side or the other, the edge that is in contact with the ice also curves.

source: Cela fait tourner le patineur. Si les patins penchent vers la droite, le patineur tourne à droite, si les patins penchent vers la gauche, le patineur tourne à gauche.
reference: This causes the skater to turn. If the skates tilt to the right, the skater turns right, if the skates tilt to the left, the skater turns left.
translation: This makes the patineur turn. If the patins turn right, the patineur turns right, if the patins turn left, the patineur turns left.

source: Pour retourner au niveau d'énergie précédent, il leur faut se débarrasser de l'excès d'énergie emmagasiné au contact de la lumière.
reference: To return to their previous energy level, they must get rid of the extra energy they got from the light.
translation: For returning to the previous energy level, they need to remove the excess energy stored in the contact with the light.

source: Ils le font en émettant une minuscule particule de lumière appelée « photon ».
reference: They do this by emitting a tiny particle of light called a "photon".
translation: They emit a tiny particle of light called a photon.

source: Les scientifiques appellent ce processus « émission stimulée de rayonnement », car les atomes sont stimulés par la lumière vive, ce qui provoque l’émission d’un photon de lumière (la lumière étant un type de rayonnement).
reference: Scientists call this process "stimulated emission of radiation" because the atoms are stimulated by the bright light, causing the emission of a photon of light, and light is a type of radiation.
translation: The scientists call this process "emission stimulated radiation", because the atoms are stimulated by the light, which causes the emission of a photon of light (the light being a type of radiation).

source: L'image suivante montre les atomes qui émettent des photons. Bien entendu en réalité les photons sont bien plus petits que ceux représentés sur l'image.
reference: The next picture shows the atoms emitting photons. Of course, in reality photons are a lot smaller than those in the picture.
translation: The image below shows the atoms emitting photons. In fact photons are much smaller than those shown in the image.

source: Les photons sont même plus petits que les particules formant les atomes !
reference: Photons are even smaller than the stuff that makes up atoms!
translation: Photons are even smaller than the particles that make up the atoms!

source: Après des centaines d'heures de fonctionnement, le filament dans l'ampoule finit par brûler et l'ampoule électrique ne marche plus.
reference: After hundreds of hours of operation the filament in the bulb eventually burns out and the light bulb no longer works.
translation: After hundreds of hours of operation, the filament in the bulb burns and the light bulb no longer works.

source: L'ampoule doit alors être remplacée. Il faut être prudent lors du changement de l'ampoule.
reference: The light bulb then needs replacing. It is necessary to be careful in replacing the light bulb.
translation: The light should then be replaced. It is important to be careful when replacing the light.

source: Tout d’abord, l’interrupteur de l’appareil d’éclairage doit être éteint ou le câble débranché.
reference: First, the switch for the light fixture needs to be turned off or the cable disconnected.
translation: First, the light switch should be turned off or the cable disconnected.

source: Cela est dû au fait que le courant électrique qui circule dans la douille, où s'encastre la partie métallique de l'ampoule, peut entraîner des chocs électriques graves si vous entrez en contact avec son intérieur ou sa base métallique alors que l'ampoule est encore partiellement insérée dans la douille.
reference: This is because electricity flowing into the socket where the metallic part of bulb sits can give you a severe electric shock if you touch the inside of the socket or the metal base of the bulb while it is still partly in the socket.
translation: This is due to the fact that the current flowing through the bulb, where the metal part of the bulb is embedded, can cause serious electrical shock if you touch the bulb or the metal part of the bulb while the bulb is still partially inserted into the bulb.

source: L'organe principal du système cardio-vasculaire est le cœur, celui-ci pompe le sang.
reference: The major organ of the circulatory system is the heart, which pumps the blood.
translation: The main organ of the cardiovascular system is the heart, which pumps the blood.

source: Le sang s'éloigne du cœur dans des tubes appelés artères et revient au cœur dans des tubes appelés veines. Les plus petits tubes sont appelés capillaires.
reference: Blood goes away from the heart in tubes called arteries and comes back to the heart in tubes called veins. The smallest tubes are called capillaries.
translation: Blood moves from the heart in tubes called arteries and returns to the heart in tubes called veins. The smallest tubes are called capillaries.

source: Une dentition de tricératops aurait été capable d'écraser non seulement des feuilles, mais également des branches et des racines très dures.
reference: A triceratops' teeth would have been able to crush not only leaves but even very tough branches and roots.
translation: A tooth of tricératops would have been able to crush not only leaves, but also branches and roots very hard.

source: Certains scientifiques pensent que le tricératops mangeait des cycadées, un type de plante qui était très courant pendant la période crétacée.
reference: Some scientists think Triceratops ate cycads, which are a type of plant that was common in the Cretaceous.
translation: Some scientists think that the tricératops ate cycad plants, a type of plant that was very common during the period of the Cretaceous.

source: Ces plantes ressemblent à un petit palmier avec une couronne de feuilles pointues et hérissées.
reference: These plants look like a small palm tree with a crown of sharp, spiky leaves.
translation: These plants look like a small palm with a long, pointed crown.

source: Un tricératops aurait pu utiliser son bec puissant pour enlever les feuilles avant de manger le tronc.
reference: A Triceratops could have used its strong beak to strip off the leaves before eating the trunk.
translation: A tricératops could have used his powerful beak to remove the leaves before eating the trunk.

source: D’autres scientifiques affirment que ces plantes sont très toxiques, il est donc peu probable qu’un dinosaure les ait mangées, même si aujourd’hui, le paresseux et d’autres animaux comme le perroquet (un descendant des dinosaures) peuvent manger des feuilles ou des fruits toxiques.
reference: Other scientists argue that these plants are very poisonous so it is unlikely that any dinosaur ate them, even though today the sloth and other animals like the parrot (a descendant of the dinosaurs) can eat poisonous leaves or fruit.
translation: Other scientists say that these plants are very toxic, so it is unlikely that a dinosaur ever ate them, even though today, the lazy and other animals like the dog (a descendant of dinosaurs) can eat toxic leaves or fruits.

source: Comment la gravité d’Io pourrait-elle m’affecter ? Si vous vous teniez sur la surface d’Io, vous pèseriez moins que sur Terre.
reference: How would Io's gravity pull on me? If you stood on the surface of Io, you would weigh less than you do on Earth.
translation: How could gravity affect me? If you stood on Io's surface, you would be less likely to fall down than on Earth.

source: Une personne qui pèse 200 livres (90kg) sur Terre pèserait environ 36 livres (16kg) sur Io. Donc la gravité, bien sûr, vous attire moins.
reference: A person who weighs 200 pounds (90kg) on Earth would weigh about 36 pounds (16kg) on Io. So the gravity, of course, pulls less on you.
translation: A person who weighs 200 pounds (90kg) on Earth would weigh about 36 pounds (16kg) on Io. So gravity, of course, attracts you less.

source: Le Soleil ne possède pas de croûte comme la Terre sur laquelle on peut se tenir debout. Le Soleil tout entier est fait de gaz, de feu et de plasma.
reference: The Sun doesn't have a crust like the Earth that you can stand on. The whole Sun is made out of gases, fire, and plasma.
translation: The Sun doesn't have a crust like the Earth on which to stand. The Sun is made of gas, fire, and plasma.

source: Le gaz se raréfie à mesure que l'on s'éloigne du centre du Soleil.
reference: The gas becomes thinner as you go farther from the center of the Sun.
translation: The gas is rarer as we get farther away from the center of the Sun.

source: La partie extérieure que nous voyons lorsque nous regardons le Soleil s’appelle la photosphère, ce qui signifie « boule de lumière ».
reference: The outer-part we see when we look at the Sun is called the photosphere, which means "ball of light".
translation: The outer part of the Sun that we see when we look at the Sun is called the photosphere, meaning "bulb of light".

source: Environ trois mille ans plus tard, en 1610, l'astronome italien Galilée utilisa un télescope pour observer que Vénus a des phases, tout comme la lune.
reference: About three thousand years later, in 1610, Italian astronomer Galileo Galilei used a telescope to observe that Venus has phases, just as the moon does.
translation: About three thousand years later, in 1610, Galileo used a telescope to observe that Venus has phases, as well as the moon.

source: Des phases se produisent parce que seul le côté de Vénus (ou de la Lune) qui fait face au Soleil est éclairé. Les phases de Vénus ont justifié la théorie de Copernic selon laquelle les planètes tournent autour du Soleil.
reference: Phases happen because only the side of Venus (or of the Moon) facing the Sun is lighted. The phases of Venus supported the theory of Copernicus that the planets go around the Sun.
translation: The phases occur because only the side of Venus (or the moon) that faces the Sun is illuminated. The phases of Venus have justified the theory of Copernicus according to which planets orbit the Sun.

source: Puis, quelques années plus tard, en 1639, un astronome anglais du nom de Jeremiah Horrocks a observé un transit de Vénus.
reference: Then, a few years later in 1639, an English astronomer named Jeremiah Horrocks observed a transit of Venus.
translation: Then, in 1639, a British astronomer named Jeremiah Horrocks observed a transit of Venus.

source: L'Angleterre avait connu une longue période de paix après la reconquête du Danelaw.
reference: England had experienced a long period of peace after the reconquest of the Danelaw.
translation: England had a long period of peace after the reconquest of the Danelaw.

source: Cependant, en 991, Ethelred a dû faire face à une flotte viking plus importante que toutes les autres depuis celle de Guthrum un siècle plus tôt.
reference: However in 991 Ethelred was faced with a Viking fleet larger than any since Guthrum's a century earlier.
translation: However, in 991 Ethelred had to face a Viking fleet larger than all the other Vikings since Guthrum's in 991.

source: Cette flotte était commandée par Olaf Trygvasson, un Norvégien qui avait l'ambition de soustraire son pays à la domination danoise.
reference: This fleet was led by Olaf Trygvasson, a Norwegian with ambitions to reclaim his country from Danish domination.
translation: The fleet was commanded by Olaf Trygvasson, a Norwegian who had ambitions to subdue Denmark.

source: Après les premiers échecs militaires, Ethereld est parventu à un accord avec Olaf, pour sa part retourné en Norvège afin d'essayer de reconquérir son royaume, pour des résultats mitigés.
reference: After initial military setbacks, Ethelred was able to agree to terms with Olaf, who returned to Norway to try to gain his kingdom with mixed success.
translation: After the first military defeats, Ethelred is now in a position to agree with Olaf, who is returning to Norway to try to regain his kingdom, with mixed results.

source: Le Hangeul est le seul alphabet inventé exprès pour être utilisé dans la vie quotidienne. L'alphabet a été inventé en 1444 sous le règne du roi Sejong (1418 – 1450).
reference: Hangeul is the only purposely invented alphabet in popular daily use. The alphabet was invented in 1444 during the reign of King Sejong (1418 – 1450).
translation: The Hangeul is the only alphabet invented for use in everyday life. The alphabet was invented in 1444 by the king Sejong (1418 - 1450).

source: Sejong le Grand fut le quatrième roi de la dynastie Joseon et demeure l’un des souverains coréens les plus respectés.
reference: King Sejong was the fourth king of the Joseon Dynasty and is one of the most highly regarded.
translation: Sejong the Great was the fourth king of the Joseon dynasty and is regarded as one of the most respected Korean kings.

source: À l’origine, il a donné à l’alphabet Hangeul le nom de Hunmin Jeongeum, qui signifie « les sons corrects pour instruire le peuple ».
reference: He originally named the Hangeul alphabet Hunmin Jeongeum, which means "the correct sounds for the instruction of the people".
translation: In the original, Hunmin Jeongeum was given the name Hunmin Jeongeum, which means "sounding correct for instruction of the people".

source: Il existe de nombreuses théories sur la façon dont le sanskrit a vu le jour. L'une d'entre elles concerne une migration aryenne de l'ouest vers l'Inde qui est venue avec sa langue.
reference: There are many theories to how Sanskrit came into existence. One of them is about an Aryan migration from the west into India who brought their language with them.
translation: There are many theories on how Sanskrit came to be. One of them is that an aryan migration from the west came with its language.

source: Le sanskrit est une langue ancienne, celle-ci est comparable à la langue latine parlée en Europe.
reference: Sanskrit is an ancient language and is comparable to the Latin language spoken in Europe.
translation: Sanskrit is an ancient language, comparable to the Latin language spoken in Europe.

source: Le plus ancien livre connu du monde a été écrit en sanskrit. Après la compilation des Upanishads, le sanskrit s'est tout simplement effacé en raison de la hiérarchie
reference: The earliest known book in the world was written in Sanskrit. After the compilation of Upanishads, Sanskrit just faded due to hierarchy.
translation: The oldest known book in the world was written in Sanskrit. After the compilation of Upanishads, Sanskrit was completely erased because of the hierarchy.

source: Le sanskrit est une langue très complexe et très riche, qui a servi de source à de nombreuses langues indiennes modernes, tout comme le latin est la source de langues européennes telles que le français et l'espagnol.
reference: Sanskrit is a very complex and rich language, which has served to be the source for many modern Indian languages, just like Latin is the source for European languages like French and Spanish.
translation: Sanskrit is a very complex and rich language, which has served as a source for many modern Indian languages, like Latin is the source of European languages such as French and Spanish.

source: Une fois la bataille pour la France terminée, l'Allemagne a commencé à se préparer à envahir l'île de Grande-Bretagne.
reference: With the battle for France over, Germany began to get ready to invade the island of Britain.
translation: Once the war for France was over, Germany began to prepare to invade the island of Britain.

source: L’Allemagne a donné le nom de code « Opération Lion de Mer » à cette attaque. L’armée britannique avait perdu la majeure partie de son artillerie lourde et de ses munitions lors de l’évacuation de Dunkerque, et était donc assez affaiblie.
reference: Germany code-named the attack “Operation Sealion”. Most of the British Army's heavy weapons and supplies had been lost when it evacuated from Dunkirk, so the army was fairly weak.
translation: The Germans gave the name of Operation Lion of the Sea to this attack. The British army had lost most of its heavy weapons and ammunition during the evacuation of Dunkerque, and was therefore very weak.

source: Mais la Royal Navy était encore beaucoup plus forte que la marine allemande (« Kriegsmarine ») et aurait pu détruire toute flotte d'invasion envoyée à travers la Manche anglaise.
reference: But the Royal Navy was still much stronger than the German Navy (“Kriegsmarine”) and could have destroyed any invasion fleet sent across the English Channel.
translation: But the Royal Navy was still much stronger than the German (“Kriegsmarine”) and could have destroyed all the invading fleet sent across the English Channel.

source: Cependant, très peu de navires de la Royal Navy étaient basés près des routes d'invasion probables car les amiraux craignaient d'être coulés par une attaque aérienne allemande.
reference: However, very few Royal Navy ships were based near the likely invasion routes as the admirals were afraid they would be sunk by German air attack.
translation: However, very few Royal Navy ships were based near the potential invasion routes because the admirals feared being sunk by German air attack.

source: Commençons par expliquer la stratégie de l'Italie, « dauphin » principal de l'Allemagne et du Japon.
reference: Let's start with an explanation about Italy's plans. Italy was mainly the "little brother" of Germany and Japan.
translation: Let's begin by explaining the strategy of Italy, the "dauphin" of Germany and Japan.

source: Leur armée et leur flotte étaient plus faibles, et ce malgré le fait qu’ils aient construit quatre nouveaux navires juste avant le début de la guerre.
reference: It had a weaker army and a weaker navy, although they had just built four new ships right before the beginning of the war.
translation: Their army and fleet were weaker than before, and this despite the fact that they built four new ships just before the start of the war.

source: Les principaux objectifs de l'Italie étaient les pays africains. Pour conquérir ces pays, il fallait disposer d'une base de lancement des troupes, afin que celles-ci puissent traverser la Méditerranée et envahir l'Afrique.
reference: Italy's main goals were African countries. To capture those countries, they would need to have a troop launching pad, so as troops could sail across the Mediterranean Sea and invade Africa.
translation: The main objectives of Italy were the African countries. To conquer these countries, it was necessary to have a launching base, so that the troops could cross the Mediterranean and invade Africa.

source: Pour cela, ils devaient se débarrasser des bases et des navires britanniques en Égypte. En dehors de ces actions, les cuirassés italiens n'étaient pas censés faire quoi que ce soit d'autre.
reference: For that, they had to get rid of British bases and ships in Egypt. Besides those actions, Italy's battleships were not supposed to do anything else.
translation: For this, they had to destroy the bases and ships of the British fleet in Egypt. Besides these actions, the Italian cuirasses were not to do anything else.

source: Passons maintenant au Japon. Le Japon est un pays insulaire, tout comme la Grande-Bretagne.
reference: Now for Japan. Japan was an island country, just like Britain.
translation: Let's now go to Japan. Japan is an island country, like the British.

source: Les sous-marins sont des navires conçus pour voyager sous l'eau et y rester pendant une longue période.
reference: Submarines are ships designed to travel underwater, and remain there for an extended amount of time.
translation: Submarines are ships designed to travel underwater and stay there for a long period of time.

source: Les sous-marins ont été utilisés pendant la Première et la Deuxième Guerre mondiale. À l’époque, ils étaient très lents et avaient une portée de tir très limitée.
reference: Submarines were used in World War I and World War II. Back then they were very slow and had a very limited shooting range.
translation: The submarines were used during the First and Second World War. At the time, they were very slow and had very limited range of action.

source: Au début de la guerre, ils voguaient essentiellement sur la mer. Mais au vu des progrès réalisés en matière de radars, et étant donné leur précision sans cesse grandissante, les sous-marins étaient obligé de passer sous l'eau pour ne pas être repérés.
reference: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.
translation: At the beginning of the war, they mostly went on the sea. But as the radar progressed and their accuracy increased, submarines were forced to go underwater to avoid being seen.

source: Les sous-marins allemands étaient appelés U-Boot. Les Allemands étaient très doués pour la navigation et le maniement de leurs sous-marins.
reference: German submarines were called U-Boats. The Germans were very good at navigating and operating their submarines.
translation: The German submarines were called U-Boot. The Germans were very skilled in navigating and using their submarines.

source: En raison de leur succès avec les sous-marins, après la guerre on ne fait pas confiance aux Allemands pour qu'ils en possèdent beaucoup.
reference: Because of their success with submarines, after the war Germans aren't trusted to have many of them.
translation: Due to their success with submarines, after the war, we don't trust the Germans to have a lot of them.

source: Oui ! Le roi Toutankhamon, parfois appelé « Roi Tout » ou « L’Enfant roi », est l’un des anciens monarques égyptiens les plus connus des temps modernes.
reference: Yes! King Tutankhamun, sometimes referred to as "King Tut" or "The Boy King", is one of the most well known ancient Egyptian kings in modern times.
translation: Yes, the King Tutankhamun, sometimes called "Royal King" or "Prince of the Ancient Egyptians", is one of the most famous ancient monks of the modern era.

source: Il est intéressant de noter qu’il n’était pas considéré comme très important dans l’Antiquité et n’était pas inscrit sur la plupart des anciennes listes de rois.
reference: Interestingly, he was not considered to be very important in ancient times and was not recorded on most ancient king lists.
translation: It is interesting to note that it was not considered very important in the ancient world and was not listed on most ancient lists of kings.

source: Cependant, la découverte de sa tombe en 1922 a fait de lui une célébrité. Alors que de nombreuses tombes du passé ont été pillées, cette tombe est restée pratiquement intacte.
reference: However, the discovery of his tomb in 1922 made him a celebrity. While many tombs of the past were robbed, this tomb was left virtually undisturbed.
translation: However, the discovery of his tomb in 1922 made him a celebrity. While many tombs of the past have been robbed, this tomb is still virtually intact.

source: La plupart des objets enterrés avec Toutankhamon ont été bien conservés, y compris des milliers d'artefacts faits de métaux précieux et de pierres rares.
reference: Most of the items buried with Tutankhamun have been well preserved, including thousands of artefacts made from precious metals and rare stones.
translation: Most of the tombs with Tutankhamun have been well preserved, including thousands of artefacts made of precious metals and rare stones.

source: L'invention des roues à rayons a rendu les chars assyriens plus légers, plus rapides et mieux préparés pour distancer les soldats et autres chars.
reference: The invention of spoke wheels made Assyrian chariots lighter, faster, and better prepared to outrun soldiers and other chariots.
translation: The invention of wheels made the Assyrians lighter, faster, and better prepared to defend themselves and other chariots.

source: Les flèches de leurs arbalètes mortelles pouvaient pénétrer l'armure des soldats rivaux. Vers 1000 avant J.-C., les Assyriens ont introduit la première cavalerie.
reference: Arrows from their deadly crossbows could penetrate the armor of rival soldiers. About 1000 B.C., the Assyrians introduced the first cavalry.
translation: The arrows of their deadly spears could penetrate the armor of their rivals. In 1000 BC, the Assyrians introduced the first cavalry.

source: Une cavalerie est une armée qui combat à cheval. La selle n'ayant pas encore été inventée, la cavalerie assyrienne se battait en montant à cru.
reference: A cavalry is an army that fights on horseback. The saddle had not yet been invented, so the Assyrian cavalry fought on the bare backs of their horses.
translation: A cavalry is a military force that fights in a horse. The horse's saddle has not yet been invented, the Assyrian cavalry fought in a bare back.

source: Nous connaissons de nombreux hommes politiques, scientifiques et artistes grecs. Mais le plus célèbre de toute cette civilisation est probablement Homère, le poète aveugle auteur des deux plus grands chefs-d'œuvre de la littérature grecque : les poèmes de l'Iliade et l'Odyssée.
reference: We know many Greek politicians, scientists, and artists. Possibly the most known person of this culture is Homer, the legendary blind poet, who composed two masterpieces of Greek literature: the poems Iliad and Odyssey.
translation: We know many Greek politicians, scientists and artists. But the most famous of all this civilisation is probably Homer's great poet, blind man, who wrote the two greatest works of Greek literature: the poems of the Iliad and Odyssey.

source: Sophocle et Aristophane sont toujours des dramaturges populaires, et leurs pièces sont considérées comme faisant partie des plus grandes œuvres de la littérature mondiale.
reference: Sophocles and Aristophanes are still popular playwrights and their plays are considered to be among the greatest works of world literature.
translation: Sophocles and Aristophanes are still popular playwrights, and their plays are considered to be among the world's greatest works of literature.

source: Un autre grec célèbre est le mathématicien Pythagore, surtout connu pour son célèbre théorème sur les relations des côtés des triangles rectangles.
reference: Another famous Greek is a mathematician Pythagoras, mostly known for his famous theorem about relations of the sides of right triangles.
translation: Another Greek famous is Pythagoras, especially known for his famous theorem on the relations of sides of rectangles triangles.

source: Les estimations sont variées quant au nombre de personnes qui parlent Hindi. On estime que c'est entre la deuxième et la quatrième langue la plus communément parlée au monde.
reference: There are varying estimates for how many people speak Hindi. It is estimated to be between the second and fourth most commonly spoken language in the world.
translation: Estimates vary on the number of people who speak Hindi. It is estimated that it's the second and fourth most commonly spoken language in the world.

source: Le nombre de langues maternelles dépend de si oui ou non les dialectes très proches sont pris en compte.
reference: The number of native speakers varies depending on whether or not very closely related dialects are counted.
translation: The number of languages spoken in a country depends on whether or not closely related dialects are taken into account.

source: Les estimations varient de 340 millions à 500 millions de locuteurs, et jusqu'à 800 millions de personnes peuvent comprendre la langue.
reference: Estimates range from 340 million to 500 million speakers, and as many as 800 million people can understand the language.
translation: Estimates range from 340 million to 500 million speakers, and up to 800 million people can understand the language.

source: L'hindi et l'ourdou disposent d'un vocabulaire semblable mais d'une écriture différente ; lors d'une conversation de tous les jours, les locuteurs des deux langues peuvent en général se comprendre.
reference: Hindi and Urdu are similar in vocabulary but different in script; in everyday conversations, speakers of both languages can usually understand each other.
translation: Hindi and Urdu have similar vocabulary but different writing; in everyday conversations, the speakers of both languages can usually understand each other.

source: Vers le 15e siècle, le nord de l’Estonie subissait une forte influence culturelle germanique.
reference: Around the 15th century, northern Estonia was under great cultural influence of Germany.
translation: The 15th century was a time of great cultural influence from the north of Estonia.

source: Certains moines allemands voulaient rapprocher Dieu des autochtones ; c’est pour cela qu’ils ont inventé la langue littérale estonienne.
reference: Some German monks wanted to bring God closer to the native people, so they invented the Estonian literal language.
translation: Some German monks wanted to make God closer to the indigenous people; this was why they invented the literal Estonian language.

source: Il était basé sur l'alphabet allemand et un caractère « Õ/õ » a été ajouté.
reference: It was based on the German alphabet and one character "Õ/õ" was added.
translation: The text was based on the German alphabet and a "Õ/õ" character was added.

source: Au fil du temps, de nombreux mots empruntés à l'allemand se sont mélangés. Ce fut le début du développement.
reference: As time passed, many words that were borrowed from German coalesced. This was the beginning of enlightenment.
translation: The word "word" has been borrowed from German for a long time. This was the beginning of the development.

source: Dans la tradition, l'héritier du trône faisait son service militaire après avoir fini ses études.
reference: Traditionally, the heir to the throne would go straight into the military after finishing school.
translation: In the tradition, the heir to the throne served as a soldier after finishing his studies.

source: Cependant, Charles est allé à l’université au Trinity College, à Cambridge, où il a étudié l’anthropologie et l’archéologie, et plus tard, l’histoire, obtenant un 2:2 (un diplôme inférieur de deuxième classe).
reference: However, Charles went to university at Trinity College, Cambridge where he studied Anthropology and Archaeology, and later History, earning a 2:2 (a lower second class degree).
translation: However, Charles went to Trinity College, Cambridge, where he studied anthropology and archaeology, and later history, and got 2:2 (a lower secondary diploma).

source: Charles fut le premier membre de la famille royale britannique à obtenir une licence.
reference: Charles was the first member of the British Royal Family to be awarded a degree.
translation: Charles was the first British monarch to obtain a degree.

source: La Turquie européenne (Thrace orientale ou Roumélie dans la péninsule balkanique) comprend 3 % du pays.
reference: European Turkey (eastern Thrace or Rumelia in the Balkan peninsula) includes 3% of the country.
translation: The Turkish European territory (Thrace oriental or Roumélie in the peninsula of Balkan) includes 3% of the country.

source: Le territoire de la Turquie est long de plus de 1600 kilomètres (1000 miles) et large de 800 kilomètres (500 miles), avec une forme plus ou moins rectangulaire.
reference: The territory of Turkey is more than 1,600 kilometres (1,000 mi) long and 800 km (500 mi) wide, with a roughly rectangular shape.
translation: The territory of Turkey is long of more than 1600 kilometres (1000 miles) and wide of 800 kilometres (500 miles), with a more or less rectangular shape.

source: La superficie de la Turquie, lacs compris, est de 783 562 kilomètres carrés, dont 755 688 kilomètres carrés en Asie du Sud-Ouest et 23 764 kilomètres carrés en Europe.
reference: Turkey's area, including lakes, occupies 783,562 square kilometres (300,948 sq mi), of which 755,688 square kilometres (291,773 sq mi) are in south west Asia and 23,764 square kilometres (9,174 sq mi) in Europe.
translation: Turkey's area is 783 562 kilometres carrés, including 755 688 kilometres carrés in the South East and 23 764 kilometres carrés in Europe.

source: La superficie de la Turquie en fait le 37e plus grand pays du monde et équivaut à peu près à la taille de la France métropolitaine et du Royaume-Uni réunis.
reference: Turkey's area makes it the world's 37th-largest country, and is about the size of Metropolitan France and the United Kingdom combined.
translation: Turkey's surface makes it the 37th largest country in the world and is roughly the size of the French metropolitan area and the UK combined.

source: La Turquie est entourée par des mers sur trois côtés : la mer Égée à l'ouest, la mer Noire au nord et la mer Méditerranée au sud.
reference: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.
translation: Turkey is surrounded by three sides: the west, the north and the south by the sea.

source: Le Luxembourg a une longue histoire, mais son indépendance ne date que de 1839.
reference: Luxembourg has a long history but its independence dates from 1839.
translation: Luxembourg has a long history, but its independence dates from 1839.

source: Certaines régions actuelles de la Belgique faisaient autrefois partie du Luxembourg, mais sont devenues belges après la Révolution belge des années 1830.
reference: Present-day parts of Belgium were part of Luxembourg in the past but became Belgian after the 1830s Belgian Revolution.
translation: Some regions of Belgium were formerly Luxembourg, but were Belgian after the Belgian Revolution of 1830.

source: Le Luxembourg a toujours essayé de rester un pays neutre, mais le territoire a été occupé par l’Allemagne pendant les Première et Seconde Guerres mondiales.
reference: Luxembourg has always tried to remain a neutral country but it was occupied in both World War I and World War II by Germany.
translation: Luxembourg has always tried to remain neutral, but the territory has been occupied by Germany during the First and Second World War.

source: En 1957, le Luxembourg est devenu l'un des membres fondateurs de l'organisme aujourd'hui connu sous le nom d'Union Européenne.
reference: In 1957 Luxembourg became a founding member of the organization which is today known as the European Union.
translation: In 1957, Luxembourg became one of the founding members of the European Union today known as the European Union.

source: Le Drukgyal Dzong est une forteresse et un monastère bouddhiste en ruine dans la partie supérieure du district de Paro (dans le village de Phondey).
reference: The Drukgyal Dzong is a ruined fortress and Buddhist monastery in the upper part of the Paro District (in Phondey Village).
translation: The Drukgyal Dzong is a ruined Buddhist monastery and a ruined fort in the upper district of Paro (in Phondey village).

source: On dit qu’en 1649, Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyel a créé la forteresse pour commémorer sa victoire sur les forces tibéto-mongoles.
reference: It is said that in 1649, Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyel created the fortress to commemorate his victory against the Tibetan-Mongol forces.
translation: In 1649, Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyel created the fort to commemorate his victory over the Mongol forces.

source: En 1951, un incendie a fait qu’il ne reste que quelques reliques des Drukgyal Dzong, comme l’image de Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyal.
reference: In 1951, a fire caused for only some of the relics of the Drukgyal Dzong to remain, such as the image of Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyal.
translation: In 1951, a fire destroyed the Drukgyal Dzong, as the image of Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyal.

source: Après l'incendie, la forteresse a été préservée et protégée, restant l'une des attractions les plus sensationnelles du Bhoutan.
reference: After the fire, the fortress was preserved and protected, remaining to be one of Bhutan's most sensational attractions.
translation: After the fire, the fort was preserved and protected, remaining one of the most spectacular attractions in the Bhoutan.

source: Au XVIIIe siècle, le Cambodge s'est retrouvé coincé entre deux puissants voisins, la Thaïlande et le Vietnam.
reference: During the 18th century Cambodia found itself squeezed between two powerful neighbors, Thailand and Vietnam.
translation: In the 18th century, Cambodia was caught between two powerful neighbors, Thailand and Vietnam.

source: Les Thaïs ont envahi le Cambodge à plusieurs reprises au XVIIIe siècle et en 1772, ils ont détruit Phnom Phen.
reference: The Thais invaded Cambodia several times in the 18th century and in 1772 they destroyed Phnom Phen.
translation: The Thai invaders invaded Cambodia in the 18th century and in 1772, they destroyed Phnom Phen.

source: À la fin du XVIIIe siècle, les Vietnamiens envahirent aussi le Cambodge.
reference: In the last years of the 18th century the Vietnamese also invaded Cambodia.
translation: In the 18th century, Vietnamese invaded Cambodia.

source: Dix-huit pour cent des Vénézuéliens sont au chômage, et la plupart de ceux qui ont un emploi travaillent dans l'économie informelle.
reference: Eighteen percent of Venezuelans are unemployed, and most of those who are employed work in the informal economy.
translation: Twenty-eight percent of Venezuelans are unemployed, and most of those who work in the informal economy are employed in the formal economy.

source: Deux tiers des Vénézuéliens qui travaillent le font dans le secteur des services, près d’un quart dans l’industrie et un cinquième dans l’agriculture.
reference: Two thirds of Venezuelans who work do so in the service sector, nearly a quarter work in industry and a fifth work in agriculture.
translation: Twenty-three percent of Venezuelans work in the services sector, nearly a quarter in the industry and a fifth in agriculture.

source: Une industrie importante pour les Vénézuéliens est le pétrole, dont le pays est un exportateur net, même si seulement un pour cent travaille dans l’industrie pétrolière.
reference: An important industry for Venezuelans is oil, where the country is a net exporter, even though only one percent work in the oil industry.
translation: A major industry for Venezuelans is oil, which is a net export for the country, even though only a quarter of the workforce works in oil industry.

source: Au lendemain de son indépendance, Singapour a acquis une expertise dans le domaine des jardins botaniques. Cet Etat insulaire s'est par la suite transformé en une cité jardin de type tropical.
reference: Early in the nation's independence, Singapore Botanic Gardens' expertise helped to transform the island into a tropical Garden City.
translation: After independence, Singapore gained expertise in botanical gardens. This island became a tropical city in the aftermath of its independence.

source: En 1981, Vanda Miss Joaquim, un hybride d'orchidée, a été choisie comme fleur emblème de la nation.
reference: In 1981, Vanda Miss Joaquim, an orchid hybrid, was chosen as the nation's national flower.
translation: In 1981, Vanda Miss Joaquim, a hybrid orchid, was chosen as the national flower of the nation.

source: Chaque année, vers le mois d’octobre, près de 1,5 million d’herbivores se dirigent vers les plaines du sud, en traversant la rivière Mara, depuis les collines du nord pour les pluies.
reference: Every year around October nearly 1.5 million herbivores travel towards the southern plains, crossing the Mara River, from the northern hills for the rains.
translation: Each year, about 1.5 million herbivores travel to the south to the Mara River, crossing the mountains from the north to the river to collect rain.

source: Et puis retour au nord par l'ouest, en traversant une fois de plus la rivière Mara, après les pluies aux environs d'avril.
reference: And then back to the north through the west, once again crossing the Mara river, after the rains in around April.
translation: Then we went north again by the west, crossing again the Mara river, after the rains in April.

source: La région du Serengeti comprend le parc national du Serengeti, la zone de conservation de Ngorongoro et la réserve de chasse des Maswa en Tanzanie, ainsi que la réserve nationale du Masai Mara au Kenya.
reference: The Serengeti region contains the Serengeti National Park, the Ngorongoro Conservation Area and Maswa Game Reserve in Tanzania and the Maasai Mara National Reserve in Kenya.
translation: The Serengeti region includes the Serengeti National Park, Ngorongoro Conservation Area and Maswa Conservation Area in Tanzania, and the Masai Mara Conservation Area in Kenya.

source: Apprendre à créer des médias interactifs nécessite des compétences conventionnelles et traditionnelles, ainsi que des outils maîtrisés dans le cadre de cours interactifs (storyboarding, montage audio et vidéo, narration d'histoires, etc.)
reference: Learning to create interactive media requires conventional and traditional skills, as well as tools mastered in interactive classes (storyboarding, audio and video editing, story telling, etc.)
translation: Interactive media requires conventional and traditional skills, as well as tools that are used in interactive classes (storyboarding, montage audio and video, narration of stories, etc.)
