reference: He would need to be judged differently if he had lost his car keys and it was his own car that he was trying to break into.
translation: It would be better if he had lost his keys and if it was his own car he tried to force it.

source: L’IRM est basée sur un phénomène physique appelé résonance magnétique nucléaire (RMN), découvert dans les années 1930 par Felix Bloch (travaillant à l’université de Stanford) et Edward Purcell (de l’université de Harvard).
reference: MRI is based on a physics phenomenon called nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR), which was discovered in the 1930s by Felix Bloch (working at Stanford University) and Edward Purcell (from Harvard University).
translation: MRI is based on a physical phenomenon called nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR), discovered in the 1930s by Felix Bloch (training at Stanford University) and Edward Purcell (from Harvard University).

source: Dans cette résonance, le champ magnétique et les ondes radio font que les atomes émettent de minuscules signaux radio.
reference: In this resonance, magnetic field and radio waves cause atoms to give off tiny radio signals.
translation: In this resonance, the magnetic field and radio waves make the atoms emit tiny radio signals.

source: En 1970, Raymond Damadian, docteur en médecine et chercheur en sciences, a découvert les bases permettant d'utiliser l'imagerie par résonance magnétique comme outil de diagnostic médical.
reference: In the year 1970, Raymond Damadian, a medical doctor and research scientist, discovered the basis for using magnetic resonance imaging as a tool for medical diagnosis.
translation: Raymond Damadian, a doctor and researcher in medical sciences, discovered the basis for using MRI as a diagnostic tool in 1970.

source: Quatre ans plus tard, un brevet a été accordé, ce qui était le premier brevet au monde délivré dans le domaine de l'IRM.
reference: Four years later a patent was granted, which was the world's first patent issued in the field of MRI.
translation: Four years later, a patent was granted, which was the first patent issued in the field of MRI.

source: En 1977, le Dr. Damadian a achevé la construction du premier scanner IRM pour tout le corps, qu'il a appelé « l'Indomptable ».
reference: In 1977, Dr. Damadian completed the construction of the first “whole-body” MRI scanner, which he called the ”Indomitable”.
translation: In 1977, Dr. Damadian completed the first MRI scanner for the whole body, he called it the "Indomitable".

source: La communication asynchrone favorise le temps de réflexion et de réaction aux autres.
reference: Asynchronous communication encourages time for reflection and reaction to others.
translation: Asynchronous communication encourages time for reflection and reaction to others.

source: Ceci permet aux étudiants de travailler à leur rythme tout en contrôlant la vitesse à laquelle leurs sont délivrées les informations pédagogiques.
reference: It allows students the ability to work at their own pace and control the pace of instructional information.
translation: This allows students to work at their own pace while controlling the speed of the information being presented.

source: De plus, il y a moins de restrictions horaires avec la possibilité de travailler avec des horaires flexibles. (Bremer, 1998)
reference: In addition, there are fewer time restrictions with the possibility of flexible working hours. (Bremer, 1998)
translation: In addition, there are fewer restrictions with the possibility of working with flexible hours. (Bremer, 1998)

source: L'utilisation d'Internet permet aux apprentis d’accéder à des informations aussi souvent qu'ils le souhaitent.
reference: The use of the Internet and the World Wide Web allows learners to have access to information at all times.
translation: The use of the Internet allows learners to access information as often as they want.

source: Les étudiants peuvent également soumettre des questions aux instructeurs à tout moment de la journée et s'attendre à des réponses raisonnablement rapides, plutôt que d'attendre la prochaine réunion en personne.
reference: Students can also submit questions to instructors at any time of day and expect reasonably quick responses, rather than waiting until the next face-to-face meeting.
translation: Students can also submit questions to instructors at any time of the day and expect reasonable answers, rather than waiting for the next meeting in person.

source: Un liberté absolue : voilà ce qu'offre l'approche post-moderne de l'apprentissage. Il n'existe pas de bonne façon d'apprendre qui serait en soi unique.
reference: The postmodern approach to learning offers the freedom from absolutes. There is no one good way to learn.
translation: A freedom of absolution: that's what the post-modern approach to learning offers. There is no way of learning that is unique.

source: En fait, il n'y a pas une seule bonne chose à apprendre. L'apprentissage se fait dans l'expérience entre l'apprenant et le savoir présenté.
reference: In fact, there is not one good thing to learn.Learning takes place in the experience between the learner and the knowledge presented.
translation: Actually, there is no one good thing to learn. Learning takes place between the learner and the presented knowledge.

source: Ce point est illustré par notre expérience actuelle de toutes les émissions télévisées informatives sur le bricolage et l'apprentissage.
reference: Our current experience with all the do-it-yourself and information presenting, learning-based television shows illustrates this point.
translation: This point is illustrated by our current experience of all informative television shows on the construction and learning.

source: Beaucoup d'entre nous se retrouvent donc en train de regarder une émission télévisée qui nous montre un processus ou une expérience à laquelle nous ne participerons jamais ni ne mettrons de connaissances en pratique.
reference: So many of us find ourselves watching a television show that informs us of a process or experience in which we will never participate or apply that knowledge.
translation: Many of us are watching a TV program that shows us a process or experience that we never will participate in or practice.

source: Nous n'allons jamais rénover une voiture, construire une fontaine dans notre arrière-cour, voyager au Pérou pour examiner des ruines antiques, ou refaire la maison de notre voisin.
reference: We will never overhaul a car, build a fountain in our backyard, travel to Peru to examine ancient ruins, or remodel our neighbour's house.
translation: We never renovate a car, build a fountain in our backyard, travel to Peru to examine ancient ruins, or build a house in our neighbor's.

source: Grâce aux liaisons par câble sous-marin à fibre optique vers l’Europe et par satellite à large bande, le Groenland est bien connecté et 93% de la population a accès à Internet.
reference: Thanks to undersea fiber optic cable links to Europe and broadband satellite, Greenland is well connected with 93% of the population having internet access.
translation: Thanks to submarine cable and fiber optic cable links to Europe and satellite broadband, Greenland is well connected and 93% of the population has access to Internet.

source: Votre hôtel, maison d’hôtes ou résidence privée proposent sûrement une connexion Wi-Fi ou un ordinateur connecté à Internet, tandis que tous les lieux disposent d'un cybercafé ou d'un endroit équipé d'une connexion Wi-Fi publique.
reference: Your hotel or hosts (if staying in a guesthouse or private home) will likely have wifi or an internet connected PC, and all settlements have an internet cafe or some location with public wifi.
translation: Your hotel, home or private residence may have a Wi-Fi or Internet connection, while all of them have a public Wi-Fi or public computer.

source: Comme mentionné ci-dessus, bien que le mot « Esquimau » reste acceptable aux États-Unis, il est considéré comme péjoratif par de nombreux peuples de l’Arctique non américains, en particulier au Canada.
reference: As mentioned above, though the word "Eskimo" remains acceptable in the United States, it is considered pejorative by many non-U.S. Arctic peoples, especially in Canada.
translation: As mentioned above, although the word "Esquimau" remains acceptable in the United States, it is considered to be a derogatory term by many peoples of the Arctic not in the United States, especially in Canada.

source: Bien que vous pouvez entendre les autochtones du Groenland utiliser le mot, les étrangers doivent éviter de l’utiliser.
reference: While you may hear the word used by Greenlandic Natives, its use should be avoided by foreigners.
translation: Although you can hear the indigenous people of Greenland use the word, foreigners should avoid using it.

source: Les habitants autochtones du Groenland se nomment Inuit au Canada et Kalaalleq (pluriel Kalaallit), Groenlandais, au Groenland.
reference: The native inhabitants of Greenland call themselves Inuit in Canada and Kalaalleq (plural Kalaallit), a Greenlander, in Greenland.
translation: The inhabitants of Greenland are known as Inuit in Canada and Kalaalleq (plural Kalaallit), Greenlandic, in Greenland.

source: "Les crimes ou les actes de malveillance en général, envers les étrangers ne sont pas de notoriété publique à Greenland. Même en ville, il n'y a pas de ""zones à risque"""
reference: Crime, and ill-will toward foreigners in general, is virtually unknown in Greenland. Even in the towns, there are no "rough areas."
translation: "Generally, crimes or malicious acts against foreigners are not of publicity in Greenland. Even in the city, there is no ""risk zone""

source: Des températures basses sont peut-être le seul vrai danger auquel devront se confronter ceux qui ne sont pas préparés.
reference: Cold weather is perhaps the only real danger the unprepared will face.
translation: Low temperatures may be the only real danger to those who are not prepared.

source: Si vous visitez le Groenland pendant les saisons froides (étant donné qu'à mesure que vous vous aventurez vers le nord, le froid s'intensifie), veillez à emporter des vêtements suffisamment chauds.
reference: If you visit Greenland during cold seasons (considering that the further north you go, the colder it will be), it is essential to bring warm enough clothing.
translation: If you visit Greenland during the cold seasons (since as you go north, the cold gets thicker), bring plenty of warm clothing.

source: Les longues journées estivales peuvent provoquer des troubles du sommeil et d'autres problèmes de santé en lien avec ces troubles.
reference: The very long days in the summer can lead to problems getting sufficient sleep and associated health issues.
translation: Summer days can cause sleep problems and other health problems related to these problems.

source: Faites également attention aux moustiques nordiques pendant l'été. Bien qu'ils ne transmettent aucune maladie, leur piqûre peut être irritante.
reference: During the summer, also watch out for the Nordic mosquitoes. Although they do not transmit any diseases, they can be irritating.
translation: Also, be aware of mosquitoes during the summer. They do not transmit any diseases, but they can be irritating.

source: Le tourisme occupe une place importante dans l'économie de San Francisco en raison de sa renommée à l'international, mais dans le fond, ses activités économiques sont diversifiées.
reference: While San Francisco's economy is linked to it being a world-class tourist attraction, its economy is diversified.
translation: Tourism is a major economic activity in San Francisco, due to its international reputation, but in the bottom, its economic activities are diversified.

source: Les principaux secteurs d'emploi sont les services professionnels, le gouvernement, la finance, le commerce et le tourisme.
reference: The largest employment sectors are professional services, government, finance, trade, and tourism.
translation: The main employment sectors are the professional services, government, finance, commerce and tourism.

source: Sa représentation fréquente dans la musique, les films, la littérature et la culture populaire a contribué à faire connaître la ville et ses monuments dans le monde entier.
reference: Its frequent portrayal in music, films, literature and popular culture has helped make the city and its landmarks known throughout the world.
translation: His frequent representation in music, films, literature and culture has helped to make the city and its monuments known throughout the world.

source: San Francisco a développé une grande infrastructure touristique avec de nombreux hôtels, restaurants et installations de congrès de premier ordre.
reference: San Francisco has developed a large tourist infrastructure with numerous hotels, restaurants, and top-notch convention facilities.
translation: San Francisco has developed a great tourism infrastructure with many hotels, restaurants and premier facilities.

source: San Francisco est aussi l'une des meilleures destinations du pays pour découvrir la cuisine asiatique : coréenne, thaï, indienne et japonaise.
reference: San Francisco is also one of the best places in the nation for other Asian cuisine: Korean, Thai, Indian, and Japanese.
translation: San Francisco is also one of the best places in the country to enjoy the Asian cuisine: Korean, Thai, Indian and Japanese.

source: Le voyage à Walt Disney World représente un pèlerinage important pour de nombreuses familles américaines.
reference: Traveling to Walt Disney World represents a major pilgrimage for many American families.
translation: Walt Disney World is a major pilgrimage for many American families.

source: La visite « typique » consiste à prendre l’avion pour l’aéroport international d’Orlando, se rendre en bus à un hôtel Disney situé sur le site, y séjourner environ une semaine sans quitter les installations Disney et rentrer chez soi.
reference: The "typical" visit involves flying into Orlando International Airport, busing to an on-site Disney hotel, spending about a week without leaving Disney property, and returning home.
translation: Typical visit consists of taking a flight to Orlando International Airport, going to a hotel in the Disney World site, staying there for a week without leaving the Disney World, and returning home.

source: Une infinité de variations sont possibles, mais c’est ce qu’entendent la plupart des gens lorsqu’ils parlent d’« aller à Disney World ».
reference: There are infinite variations possible, but this remains what most people mean when they talk of "going to Disney World".
translation: A variety of variations are possible, but the majority of people who talk about going to Disney World say it is "going to Disneyland."

source: De nombreux billets vendus en ligne sur des sites d'enchères tels que eBay ou Craigslist sont des billets valables dans les parcs pendant plusieurs jours mais déjà partiellement utilisés.
reference: Many tickets sold online through auction websites such as eBay or Craigslist are partially used multi-day park-hopper tickets.
translation: Many online auction sites such as eBay or Craigslist sell tickets for days in the park but are already partially used.

source: Bien que cette activité soit très courante, elle est interdite par Disney : les billets ne sont pas transférables.
reference: While this is a very common activity, it is prohibited by Disney: the tickets are non-transferable.
translation: Although this activity is very common, it is prohibited by Disney: tickets cannot be exchanged.

source: Pour camper sous le niveau du Grand Canyon, il vous faut un permis d’arrière-pays.
reference: Any camping below the rim in Grand Canyon requires a backcountry permit.
translation: For camping under the Grand Canyon, you need a permit.

source: Les permis, délivrés en nombre limité en vue de préserver le canyon, sont mis à disposition dès le premier du mois, quatre mois avant le départ.
reference: Permits are limited to protect the canyon, and become available on the 1st day of the month, four months prior to the start month.
translation: The permits, issued in limited numbers to protect the canyon, are available on the first day of the month, four months before the start of the trip.

source: Ainsi, un permis d’entrée dans l’arrière-pays pour toute date de début au cours du mois de mai devient valable le 1er janvier.
reference: Thus, a backcountry permit for any start date in May becomes available on 1 Jan.
translation: Thus, a permit to enter the backcountry for any start date in May becomes valid on January 1st.

source: Les places dans les endroits les plus populaires tels que le Bright Angel Campground, voisin du Phantom Ranch, sont généralement remplies par les demandes reçues à la première date d'ouverture des réservations.
reference: Space for the most popular areas, such as the Bright Angel Campground adjacent to Phantom Ranch, generally fill up by the requests received on first date they are opened to reservations.
translation: The most popular places to stay in the area such as Bright Angel Campground, the Phantom Ranch, are usually filled with requests received at the first day of reservation.

source: Les permis sont en nombre limité et sont réservés aux personnes qui se présentent sur place, suivant le principe du premier arrivé, premier servi.
reference: There are a limited number permits reserved for walk-in requests available on a first come, first served basis.
translation: The permits are limited and are reserved for those who arrive on site, following the principle of first come, first served.

source: Entrer en Afrique australe en voiture est un moyen incroyable de voir toute la beauté de la région, aussi bien que pour se rendre à des endroits hors des routes touristiques normales.
reference: Entering Southern Africa by car is an amazing way to see all the region's beauty as well as to get to places off the normal tourist routes.
translation: Travelling to Africa in a car is a great way to see the beauty of the region, as well as to see the tourist routes.

source: Cela peut se faire dans une voiture normale avec une planification minutieuse, mais un 4x4 est fortement conseillé et de nombreux endroits ne sont accessibles qu'avec un 4x4 à empattement long.
reference: This can be done in a normal car with careful planning but a 4x4 is highly advised and many locations are only accessible with a high wheel base 4x4.
translation: This can be done in a normal car with a thorough planning, but a 4x4 is highly recommended and many places are not accessible with a 4x4 with a long axle.

source: Lors de la planification, gardez à l’esprit que, bien que l’Afrique australe soit stable, tous les pays voisins ne le sont pas.
reference: Keep in mind while planning that although Southern Africa is stable not all neighboring countries are.
translation: In planning, keep in mind that although the Afar region is stable, all neighboring countries are not.

source: Les obligations de visa et les frais afférents varient d'un pays à l'autre, et dépendent du pays d'où vous venez.
reference: Visa requirements and costs vary from nation to nation and are affected by the country you come from.
translation: Visa obligations and fees vary from country to country, and depend on the country you are from.

source: Chaque pays a également des lois uniques exigeant quels produits de premier secours doivent être dans la voiture.
reference: Each country also has unique laws requiring what emergency items need to be in the car.
translation: Each country also has unique laws requiring what first aid products must be in the car.

source: Victoria Falls est une ville située dans la partie occidentale du Zimbabwe, de l'autre côté de la frontière avec Livingstone, en Zambie, et près du Botswana.
reference: Victoria Falls is a town in the western portion of Zimbabwe, across the border from Livingstone, Zambia, and near Botswana.
translation: Victoria Falls is a city in the western part of Zimbabwe, in the western part of Livingstone, Zambia and near Botswana.

source: La ville est située juste à côté des chutes, qui constituent l’attraction principale, mais cette destination touristique populaire offre aux amateurs d’aventure aussi bien qu’aux touristes de nombreuses possibilités pour un séjour prolongé.
reference: The town lies immediately next to the falls, and they are the major attraction, but this popular tourist destination offers both adventure seekers and sightseers plenty of opportunities for a longer stay.
translation: The city is just a short distance from the falls, which are the main attraction, but this popular tourist destination offers a variety of activities for all kinds of people, including those interested in adventure and those who are interested in staying longer.

source: Pendant la saison des pluies (de novembre à mars), le volume d'eau sera plus élevé et les chutes seront plus dramatiques.
reference: In the rainy season (November to March), the water volume will be higher and the Falls will be more dramatic.
translation: During the rainy season (November to March), the volume of water will be higher and the falls will be more dramatic.

source: Vous êtes sûr de vous faire mouiller si vous traversez le pont ou si vous marchez le long des pistes qui serpentent près des chutes.
reference: You are guaranteed to get wet if you cross the bridge or walk along the trails winding near the Falls.
translation: You are sure to get wet if you cross the bridge or if you walk along the tracks near the falls.

source: D'un autre côté, c'est bien parce que le volume d'eau est extrêmement élevé que la vue des chutes en sera obstruée !
reference: On the other hand, it is precisely because the volume of water is so high that your viewing of the actual Falls will be obscured—by all the water!
translation: On the other hand, the high water level is so high that the view of the falls will be obstructed.

source: Le tombeau de Toutankhamon (KV62). KV62 est peut-être la plus célèbre des tombes de la vallée, le lieu où Howard Carter a découvert en 1922 la sépulture royale presque intacte du jeune roi.
reference: Tomb of Tutankhamun (KV62). KV62 may be the most famous of the tombs in the Valley, the scene of Howard Carter's 1922 discovery of the almost intact royal burial of the young king.
translation: Tomb of Tutankhamun (KV62). KV62 is probably the most famous tomb in the valley, the place where Howard Carter discovered the royal tomb almost intact in 1922.

source: Cependant, comparé à la plupart des autres tombes royales, le tombeau de Toutankhamon ne vaut guère la peine d'être visité, étant beaucoup plus petit et avec une décoration limitée.
reference: Compared to most of the other royal tombs, however, the tomb of Tutankhamun is barely worth visiting, being much smaller and with limited decoration.
translation: However, compared to most other tombs of royalty, the tomb of Tutankhamun is not worth visiting, being much smaller and with limited decoration.

source: Toute personne souhaitant voir les traces des dommages causés à la momie lors des tentatives de la retirer du cercueil sera déçue car seules la tête et les épaules sont visibles.
reference: Anyone interested in seeing evidence of the damage to the mummy done during attempts to remove it from the coffin will be disappointed as only the head and shoulders are visible.
translation: All people interested in seeing the damage caused to the mommy during attempts to remove the coffin will be disappointed, as only the head and shoulders are visible.

source: Les fabuleuses richesses du tombeau n’y sont plus présentes, mais ont été transférées au musée égyptien du Caire.
reference: The fabulous riches of the tomb are no longer in it, but have been removed to the Egyptian Museum in Cairo.
translation: The fabulous riches of the tomb have been lost, but have been moved to the Egyptian Museum in Cairo.

source: Les visiteurs dont le temps est limité feraient mieux d'aller le passer ailleurs.
reference: Visitors with limited time would be best to spend their time elsewhere.
translation: Visitors with limited time should go elsewhere.

source: Phnom Krom, à 12 km de Siem Reap. Ce temple situé au sommet d'une colline a été érigé à la fin du IXe siècle, sous le règne du roi Yasovarman.
reference: Phnom Krom, 12 km southwest of Siem Reap. This hilltop temple was built at the end of the 9th century, during the reign of King Yasovarman.
translation: Phnom Krom, 12 km from Siem Reap. This temple was built in the late 9th century under the reign of Yasovarman.

source: L'atmosphère lugubre du temple et la vue sur le lac Tonlé Sap rendent la montée vers la colline intéressante.
reference: The gloomy atmosphere of the temple and the view over the Tonle Sap lake make the climb to the hill worthwhile.
translation: The gloomy atmosphere of the temple and the view of Tonle Sap make the climb to the hill interesting.

source: La visite du site peut être agréablement associée à une promenade en bateau sur le lac.
reference: A visit to the site can be conveniently combined with a boat trip to the lake.
translation: The visit to the site can be pleasantly combined with a boat trip on the lake.

source: Le passe Angkor est obligatoire pour pénétrer dans le temple, alors n'oubliez pas de prendre votre passeport en vous rendant au Tonlé Sap.
reference: The Angkor Pass is needed to enter the temple so do not forget to bring your passport along when heading to Tonle Sap.
translation: Angkor Pass is required to enter the temple, so don't forget to take your passport when you go to Tonle Sap.

source: Jérusalem est la capitale et la plus grande ville d’Israël, bien que la plupart des autres pays et les Nations Unies ne la reconnaissent pas comme telle.
reference: Jerusalem is the capital and largest city of Israel, though most other countries and the United Nations do not recognize it as Israel's capital.
translation: Jerusalem is the capital and largest city of Israel, although most other countries and the United Nations don't recognize it as such.

source: La cité antique des collines de Judée a une histoire fascinante qui s'étend sur des milliers d'années.
reference: The ancient city in the Judean Hills has a fascinating history spanning thousands of years.
translation: The ancient city of Judah has a fascinating history that extends thousands of years.

source: La ville est sainte pour les trois religions monothéistes - le judaïsme, le christianisme et l'islam - et sert de centre spirituel, religieux et culturel.
reference: The city is holy to the three monotheistic religions - Judaism, Christianity and Islam, and serves as a spiritual, religious, and cultural center.
translation: The city is holy for three religions - Judaism, Christianity and Islam - and serves as a spiritual, religious and cultural center.

source: L'importance religieuse de la ville, et en particulier celle des nombreux sites de la vieille ville, fait de Jérusalem l'une des principales destinations touristiques en Israël.
reference: Due to the religious significance of the city, and in particular the many sites of the Old City area, Jerusalem is one of the main tourist destinations in Israel.
translation: The religious importance of the city, and particularly the many sites of the old city, makes Jerusalem one of the main tourist destinations in Israel.

source: Jérusalem compte de nombreux sites historiques, archéologiques et culturels ainsi que des centres commerciaux, cafés et restaurants animés et très fréquentés.
reference: Jerusalem has many historic, archeological and cultural sites, along with vibrant and crowded shopping centers, cafés, and restaurants.
translation: Jerusalem has many historic, archaeological and cultural sites, as well as a number of shopping centers, cafes and restaurants that are very busy and well attended.

source: L'Équateur exige que les ressortissants cubains obtiennent une lettre de recommandation avant de pouvoir entrer en Équateur par les aéroports internationaux ou les postes-frontières.
reference: Ecuador requires that Cuban citizens receive an invitation letter prior to entering Ecuador through international airports or frontier admission points.
translation: Ecuador requires that citizens of Cuba obtain a letter of recommendation before entering Ecuador by international airports or border posts.

source: Cette lettre doit être légalisée par le Ministère des affaires étrangères équatorien et respecter certaines conditions.
reference: This letter must be legalized by the Ecuadorian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and comply with certain requirements.
translation: This letter must be legalized by the Ecuadorian Ministry of Foreign Affairs and comply with certain conditions.

source: Ces exigences visent à assurer un flux migratoire organisé entre les deux pays.
reference: These requirements are designed to provide an organized migratory flow between both countries.
translation: These requirements aim to ensure organized migration between the two countries.

source: Les citoyens cubains titulaires d'une carte verte américaine doivent se rendre dans un consulat équatorien pour obtenir une dérogation à cette exigence.
reference: Cuban citizens who are US green card holders should visit an Ecuadorian Consulate to obtain an exemption to this requirement.
translation: The citizens of the United States who are citizens of the United States with a green card must visit a consulate in Ecuador to obtain a green card exemption.

source: Votre passeport doit être valide pendant au moins six mois au-delà de vos dates de voyage. Un billet aller-retour est nécessaire pour prouver la durée de votre séjour.
reference: Your passport must be valid for at least 6 months beyond your travel dates. A round/onward trip ticket is needed to prove the length of your stay.
translation: Your passport must be valid for at least 6 months beyond your travel dates. A one-way ticket is required to prove your stay.

source: Les visites sont moins chères pour les grands groupes, donc si vous êtes seul ou avec un seul ami, essayez de rencontrer d’autres personnes et de former un groupe de quatre à six personnes pour obtenir un meilleur tarif par personne.
reference: Tours are cheaper for larger groups, so if you're by yourself or with just one friend, try to meet other people and form a group of four to six for a better per-person rate.
translation: Visits are cheaper for groups of four or six people, so if you are alone or with a single friend, try to meet other people and form a group of four to six people to get a better price per person.

source: Cependant, cela ne devrait pas trop vous inquiéter, car les touristes sont souvent mélangés pour remplir les voitures.
reference: However, this shouldn't really be off your concern, because often tourists are shuffled around to fill the cars.
translation: However, this shouldn't be too much of a worry, as tourists often mix up cars for filling up the cars.

source: Il semblerait qu'il s'agisse d'une façon de faire croire aux gens qu'ils doivent payer plus cher.
reference: It seems actually to be more a way of tricking people into believing they have to pay more.
translation: It seems to be a way of telling people that they have to pay more.

source: Cette montagne escarpée, qui domine l'extrémité nord du Machu Picchu, sert souvent de toile de fond à de nombreuses photos des ruines.
reference: Towering above the north end of Machu Picchu is this steep mountain, often the backdrop to many photos of the ruins.
translation: This mountain peak, which rises on the north end of Machu Picchu, is often used as a backdrop for many photos of the ruins.

source: Cela semble un peu intimidant d'en bas, et c'est une ascension raide et difficile, mais les personnes les plus en forme devraient pouvoir le faire en 45 minutes environ.
reference: It looks a bit daunting from below, and it is a steep and difficult ascent, but most reasonably fit persons should be able to make it in about 45 minutes.
translation: This seems a little intimidating to the bottom, and it's a steep climb and difficult, but the most fit people should be able to do it in 45 minutes.

source: Des marches en pierre sont posées le long de la plupart du chemin, et des câbles en acier offrent une rampe de soutien dans les sections les plus raides.
reference: Stone steps are laid along most of the path, and in the steeper sections steel cables provide a supporting handrail.
translation: The paths are mostly stone and the cables are made of steel to provide support in the most difficult sections.

source: Ceci étant dit, attendez-vous à être à bout de souffle et soyez vigilant dans les portions les plus raides, surtout en cas d'humidité, car cela peut très vite mal tourner.
reference: That said, expect to be out of breath, and take care in the steeper portions, especially when wet, as it can become dangerous quickly.
translation: So, wait for it to be over and be careful in the roughest sections, especially in the dryer, as it can very quickly turn.

source: Près du sommet, il faut traverser une petite grotte plutôt exiguë et dont le plafond est assez bas.
reference: There's a tiny cave near the top that must be passed through, it is quite low and a rather tight squeeze.
translation: Near the top, it is necessary to cross a small cave, which is rather narrow and has a rather low ceiling.

source: La meilleure façon de voir les sites et la faune des Galápagos est de prendre le bateau, comme l’a fait Charles Darwin en 1835.
reference: Seeing the sites and wildlife of the Galapagos is best done by boat, just as Charles Darwin did it in 1835.
translation: The best way to see the Galapagos is to take a boat, as did Charles Darwin in 1835.

source: Plus de 60 bateaux de croisière sillonnent les eaux des Galápagos, dont la taille varie de 8 à 100 passagers.
reference: Over 60 cruise ships ply the Galapagos waters - ranging in size from 8 to 100 passengers.
translation: 60 cruise ships cross the Galapagos, with a variety of sizes ranging from 8 to 100 passengers.

source: La plupart des gens réservent leur place bien à l’avance (car les bateaux sont généralement pleins pendant la haute saison).
reference: Most people book their place well in advance (as the boats are usually full during the high season).
translation: Most people book their place well in advance (because boats are usually full during the high season).

source: Assurez-vous que l'agent par lequel vous réservez est un spécialiste des Galapagos ayant une solide connaissance d'une grande variété de navires.
reference: Be sure the agent through whom you book is a Galapagos specialist with a good knowledge of a wide variety of ships.
translation: Ensure that the agent you are looking for is a specialist in Galapagos with a solid knowledge of a great variety of ships.

source: Cela permettra de trouver le navire le mieux adapté à vos intérêts et/ou contraintes spécifiques.
reference: This will ensure that your particular interests and/or constraints are matched with the ship most suitable to them.
translation: This will help you find the best vessel for your needs and/or specific requirements.

source: Avant l’arrivée des Espagnols au XVIe siècle, le nord du Chili était sous la domination inca tandis que les indigènes araucaniens (Mapuche) habitaient le centre et le sud du Chili.
reference: Before the Spanish arrived in the 16th century, northern Chile was under Inca rule while the indigenous Araucanians (Mapuche) inhabited central and southern Chile.
translation: Before the arrival of the Spanish in the 16th century, the north of Chile was under Inca rule while the araucans (Mapuche) inhabited the north and south of Chile.

source: Les Mapuches ont également été l’un des derniers groupes indigènes américains indépendants, qui n’ont été entièrement absorbés par la domination hispanophone qu’après l’indépendance du Chili.
reference: The Mapuche were also one of the last independent American indigenous groups, that were not fully absorbed into Spanish-speaking rule until after Chile's independence.
translation: Mapuche also were the last remaining indigenous American group that was completely absorbed by the Spanish domination after the Chilean independence.

source: Bien que le Chili ait déclaré son indépendance en 1810 (pendant les guerres napoléoniennes qui ont laissé l'Espagne sans gouvernement central opérationnel pendant environ deux ans), la victoire décisive sur les Espagnols n'a pas été obtenue avant 1818.
reference: Although Chile declared independence in 1810 (amid the Napoleonic wars that left Spain without a functioning central government for a couple of years), decisive victory over the Spanish was not achieved until 1818.
translation: Although Chile declared independence in 1810 (in the Napoleonic Wars that left Spain without a functioning central government for two years), the decisive victory over the Espaniards was not achieved until 1818.

source: La République dominicaine (República Dominicana en espagnol) est un pays des Caraïbes qui occupe la moitié est de l'île d'Hispaniola, qu'il partage avec Haïti.
reference: The Dominican Republic (Spanish: República Dominicana) is a Caribbean country that occupies the eastern half of the island of Hispaniola, which it shares with Haiti
translation: The Dominican Republic (Spanish: República Dominicana) is a country in the Caribbean region that occupies half of the island of Hispaniola, which it shares with Haiti.

source: En dehors des plages de sable blanc et des paysages de montagne, le pays héberge la plus ancienne ville européenne des Amériques, qui font aujourd'hui partie de Saint-Domingue.
reference: Besides white sand beaches and mountain landscapes, the country is home to the oldest European city in the Americas, now part of Santo Domingo.
translation: Beyond the white sandy beaches and the mountainous landscapes, the country houses the oldest European city in the Americas, which today forms part of Saint-Domingue.

source: L’île fut en premier lieu habitée par les Taínos et les Caribes. Ces dernier peuple parlait l'Arawakan ; il serait arrivé environ dix mille ans av. J.-C.
reference: The island was first inhabited by the Taínos and Caribes. The Caribes were an Arawakan-speaking people who had arrived around 10,000 BCE.
translation: The island was first inhabited by the Taínos and the Caribes. These last people spoke the Arawakan language; it was about ten thousand years ago that the first settlers arrived.

source: En quelques années à peine après l'arrivée des explorateurs européens, la population d'indigènes Taïnos avait considérablement diminué du fait des conquistadors espagnols.
reference: Within a few short years following the arrival of European explorers, the population of Tainos had significantly been reduced by the Spanish conquerors
translation: In just a few years after the arrival of European explorers, the population of Taíno people had greatly decreased due to Spanish conquerors.

source: D'après le frère Bartolomé de las Casas (Tratado de las Indias), entre 1492 et 1498, les conquistadors espagnols auraient tué environ 100 000 Taínos.
reference: Based on Fray Bartolomé de las Casas (Tratado de las Indias) between 1492 and 1498 the Spanish conquerors killed around 100,000 Taínos.
translation: According to the brother Bartolomé de las Casas (Tratado de las Indias), between 1492 and 1498, the Spanish conquerors had killed about 100,000 Taínos.

source: Jardín de la Unión. Cet espace a été construit en tant qu'atrium d'un couvent du XVIIe siècle, dont le Templo de San Diego est le seul bâtiment survivant.
reference: Jardín de la Unión. This space was built as the atrium for a 17th-century convent, of which the Templo de San Diego is the sole surviving building.
translation: Jardín de la Unión. This space was built as an atrium of a 17th-century convent, which is the only surviving building.

source: Il fonctionne maintenant comme la place centrale, et il y a toujours beaucoup de choses qui se passent, de jour comme de nuit.
reference: It now functions as the central plaza, and always has a lot of things going on, day and night.
translation: Now it works as the central plaza and there are always lots of things going on, day and night.

source: On peut trouver un grand nombre de restaurants autour du jardin, et des concerts gratuits ont souvent lieu l'après-midi et le soir depuis le kiosque central.
reference: There are a number of restaurants surrounding the garden, and in the afternoons and evening there free concerts are often given from the central gazebo.
translation: There are many restaurants around the garden, and concerts are often held on the afternoon and evening after the kiosk.

source: Callejon del Beso (l’allée du baiser). Deux balcons séparés par seulement 69 centimètres abritent une ancienne légende d’amour.
reference: Callejon del Beso (Alley of the Kiss). Two balconies separated by only 69 centimeters is home of an old love legend.
translation: Callejon del Beso (the kissing lane). Two balconies separated by only 69 centimeters are separated by a former legend of love.

source: Pour quelques pièces de monnaie, des enfants vous raconteront l’histoire.
reference: For a few pennies some children will tell you the story.
translation: For a few pennies, children will tell you the story.

source: Bowen Island est une excursion populaire d'une journée ou d'un week-end qui propose du kayak, des randonnées, des boutiques, des restaurants, et plus encore.
reference: Bowen Island is a popular day trip or weekend excursion offering kayaking, hiking, shops, restaurants, and more.
translation: Bowen Island is a popular day or weekend excursion that offers kayaking, hiking, restaurants, boutiques, and more.

source: Cette communauté authentique se trouve à Howe Sound, juste à côté de Vancouver, et elle est facilement accessible par des bateaux-taxis qui partent régulièrement de Granville Island, dans le centre-ville de Vancouver.
reference: This authentic community is located in Howe Sound just off Vancouver, and is easily accessed via scheduled water taxis departing Granville Island in downtown Vancouver.
translation: This authentic community is located just off Howe Sound, just off Vancouver Island, and is easily accessible by boat taxis that depart regularly from Granville Island, in the downtown Vancouver area.

source: Pour ceux qui aiment les activités de plein air, une randonnée dans le couloir Sea to Sky est indispensable.
reference: For those who enjoy outdoor activities, a trek up the Sea to Sky corridor is essential.
translation: For those who enjoy outdoor activities, a hike in the Sea to Sky corridor is essential.

source: Whistler (à une heure et demi de route partant de Vancouver) est cher, mais s'est fait connaître grâce aux Jeux olympiques d'hiver de 2010.
reference: Whistler (1.5 hour drive from Vancouver) is expensive but well-known because of the 2010 Winter Olympics.
translation: Whistler (about an hour and a half from Vancouver) is expensive, but has been popular with the 2010 Winter Olympics.

source: En hiver, profitez de certaines des meilleurs pistes de skis d'Amérique du Nord et, en été, goûtez à d'authentiques randonnées en VTT.
reference: In the winter, enjoy some of the best skiing in North America, and in the summer try some authentic mountain biking.
translation: In winter, enjoy some of the best skiing in the Americas and, in summer, enjoy some of the best biking trails.

source: Les permis doivent être réservés à l'avance. Vous devez avoir un permis pour passer la nuit au Sirena.
reference: Permits must be reserved in advance. You must have a permit to stay overnight at Sirena.
translation: The permits must be reserved in advance. You must have a permit to stay at Sirena.

source: Sirena est le seul poste de gardes forestiers qui offre un hébergement en dortoir et des repas chauds en plus du camping. La Leona, San Pedrillo et Los Patos n'offrent que des emplacements de camping sans service de restauration.
reference: Sirena is the only ranger station that offers dormitory lodging and hot meals in addition to camping. La Leona, San Pedrillo, and Los Patos offer only camping with no food service.
translation: Sirena is the only forest guard station that offers a camping and hot meals in addition to a sleeping area. The Leona, San Pedrillo and Los Patos only offer camping without a restaurant.

source: Il est possible d’obtenir des permis d'accès au parc directement depuis la station de gardes forestiers de Puerto Jiménez, mais les cartes de crédit ne sont pas acceptées.
reference: It is possible to secure park permits directly from the Ranger Station in Puerto Jiménez, but they do not accept credit cards
translation: It is possible to obtain access to the park directly from the Ranger Station of Puerto Jiménez, but credit cards are not accepted.

source: Le bureau du parc (MINAE) ne délivre pas de permis plus d’un mois avant l’arrivée prévue.
reference: The Park Service (MINAE) does not issue park permits more than one month in advance of anticipated arrival.
translation: The park office (MINAE) does not issue permits more than one month before the anticipated arrival.

source: CafeNet El Sol propose un service de réservation pour un montant de 30 dollars, ou 10 dollars pour un forfait d'une journée ; en savoir plus sur leur page Corcovado.
reference: CafeNet El Sol offers a reservation service for a fee of US$30, or $10 for one-day passes; details on their Corcovado page.
translation: CafeNet El Sol offers a 30 dollar reservation for a day or a forfait of one day; in addition, they have a Corcovado page.

source: L'archipel des îles Cook est un État en libre association avec la Nouvelle-Zélande, situé en Polynésie, au milieu de l'océan Pacifique sud.
reference: The Cook Islands are an island country in free association with New Zealand, located in Polynesia, in the middle of the South Pacific Ocean.
translation: The Cook Islands are an independent state in association with the New Zealand, located in the Polynesian archipelago, in the South Pacific Ocean.

source: Il s'agit d'un archipel de 15 îles réparties sur 2,2 millions de km carrés d'océan.
reference: It is an archipelago with 15 islands spread out over 2.2 million km2 of ocean.
translation: It is a 15 island archipelago that covers 2.2 million km2 of ocean.

source: Avec le même fuseau horaire qu’Hawaï, les îles sont parfois considérées comme « Hawaï de l’Océanie ».
reference: With the same time zone as Hawaii, the islands are sometimes thought of as "Hawaii down under".
translation: With the same time zone as Hawaii, the islands are sometimes considered "Hawaii of the West".

source: Bien que plus petite, elle rappelle à certains visiteurs âgés l'île d'Hawaii avant qu'elle ne devienne un État avec de nombreux grands hôtels touristiques et aménagements.
reference: Though smaller, it reminds some elderly visitors of Hawaii before statehood without all the large tourist hotels and other development.
translation: Although smaller, it reminds some visitors of Hawaii before it became a state with many large hotels and tourist attractions.

source: Aucune ville sur les îles Cook mais elles sont composées de 15 îles différentes. Les principales s’appellent Rarotonga et Aitutaki.
reference: The Cook Islands do not have any cities but are composed of 15 different islands. The main ones are Rarotonga and Aitutaki.
translation: No city on the Cook Islands but they are made up of 15 different islands. The main ones are Rarotonga and Aitutaki.

source: Aujourd'hui, dans les pays développés, l'offre de chambres d'hôtes de luxe a été élevée à une sorte de forme artistique.
reference: In developed countries today, providing deluxe bed and breakfasts has been raised to a sort of art-form.
translation: Today, in developed countries, luxury hotels have become art form.

source: Dans le haut de gamme, les chambres d’hôtes se font évidemment concurrence principalement sur deux points : la literie et le petit déjeuner.
reference: At the top end, B&Bs obviously compete mainly on two main things: bedding and breakfast.
translation: In the top of the range, the hostels are obviously competing mainly on two main points, the bed and breakfast and the breakfast.

source: En conséquence, il est possible de trouver dans les meilleurs établissements de cette catégorie une literie extrêmement luxueuse, comme par exemple un édredon fait main ou un lit ancien.
reference: Accordingly, at the finest such establishments one is apt to find the most luxurious bedding, maybe a handmade quilt or an antique bed.
translation: Accordingly, it is possible to find in the best hotels of this category a luxurious bed, such as a handmade or old-fashioned bed.

source: Le petit déjeuner peut comprendre des délices de saison de la région ou le plat de spécialité de l’hôte.
reference: Breakfast may include seasonal delights of the region or the host's speciality dish.
translation: Breakfast can include seasonal delights from the region or the special dish of the host.

source: Le cadre pourrait être un vieux bâtiment historique avec des meubles anciens, un terrain entretenu et une piscine.
reference: The setting might be an historic old building with antique furnishings, manicured grounds and a swimming pool.
translation: The frame might be a historic building with old furniture, a well maintained yard, and a swimming pool.

source: Monter dans sa propre voiture et partir pour un long voyage a un attrait intrinsèque dans sa simplicité.
reference: Getting into your own car and heading off on a long road trip has an intrinsic appeal in its simplicity.
translation: The following text translates into French: Monter dans sa propre voiture et partir pour un long voyage est intrinsèquement lié à sa simplicité.

source: Contrairement aux gros véhicules, vous êtes probablement déjà familiarisé avec la conduite de votre voiture et connaissez ses limites.
reference: Unlike larger vehicles, you are probably already familiar with driving your car and know its limitations.
translation: Unlike the big cars, you probably already know the rules of the road and know its limits.

source: Installer sa tente sur une propriété privée ou dans une ville, quelle qu'en soit la taille, peut facilement attirer l'attention.
reference: Setting up a tent on private property or in a town of any size can easily attract unwanted attention.
translation: Installer a tent on a private property or a city, whether large or small, can easily attract attention.

source: En bref, utiliser votre voiture est un excellent moyen de faire un voyage par la route, mais rarement en soi un moyen de « camper ».
reference: In short, using your car is a great way to take a road trip but seldom in itself a way to "camp".
translation: In short, using your car is a great way to travel by road, but seldom a good way to "go camping."

source: Le camping en voiture est possible si vous disposez d'un grand monospace, d'un SUV, d'une berline ou d'un break avec des sièges qui s'allongent.
reference: Car camping is possible if you have a large minivan, SUV, Sedan or Station Wagon with seats that lay down.
translation: Camping in a car is possible if you have a large SUV, a minivan, a break with seats that stretch out.

source: Certains hôtels conservent leur héritage remontant à l'âge d'or des trains à vapeur et des paquebots transatlantiques du XIXe siècle et début du XXe, avant la Deuxième guerre mondiale.
reference: Some hotels have a heritage from the golden age of steam railways and ocean liners; before the Second World War, in the 19th or early 20th centuries.
translation: Some hotels have their heritage from the age of steam trains and transatlantic steam-boat voyages of the 19th century and early 20th century, before the Second World War.

source: Ces hôtels accueillaient les nantis et les célébrités de l'époque, et on y donnait régulièrement de somptueux dîners et de superbes réceptions.
reference: These hotels were where the rich and the famous of the day would stay, and often had fine dining and nightlife.
translation: These hotels were frequented by rich and famous people of the time, and they were often attended by fine dining and great receptions.

source: L'aménagement vieillot, l'absence d'équipements récents et un certain charme à l'ancienne font également partie de leur caractère.
reference: The old fashioned fittings, the lack of the latest amenities, and a certain graceful agedness are also part of their character.
translation: The old-fashioned layout, outdated equipment, and a certain charm to the old make them also part of their charm.

source: Bien qu’ils soient le plus souvent privés, certains accueillent parfois des chefs d’État ou d’autres dignitaires.
reference: While they are usually privately owned, they sometimes accommodate visiting heads of state and other dignitaries.
translation: They are often privately owned, but sometimes they host dignitaries or other government officials.

source: Le voyageur qui dispose de sommes considérables peut envisager un tour du monde en avion, entrecoupé de séjours dans nombre de ces hôtels.
reference: A traveller with piles of money might consider a round the world flight, broken up with stays in many of these hotels.
translation: The traveler who has large sums of money can consider a trip to the world in a plane, with a few stops in many of these hotels.

source: Un réseau d’échange d’hospitalité est l’organisation qui met en relation les voyageurs avec les habitants des villes qu’ils vont visiter.
reference: A hospitality exchange network is the organization that connects travelers with locals in the cities they are going to visit.
translation: A hospitality exchange network is the organization that connects travellers with the inhabitants of the cities they are going to visit.

source: Rejoindre un tel réseau ne nécessite généralement que de remplir un formulaire en ligne ; bien que certains réseaux proposent ou nécessitent une vérification complémentaire.
reference: Joining such a network usually just requires filling out an online form; although some networks offer or require additional verification.
translation: Join such a network is usually only required to fill out a form online; however, some networks require or require additional verification.

source: Une liste des hôtes disponibles est ensuite fournie soit en version imprimée et / ou en ligne, parfois avec des références et des avis d'autres voyageurs.
reference: A listing of available hosts is then provided either in print and/or online, sometimes with references and reviews by other travelers.
translation: A list of available hosts is then provided either in print or online, sometimes with references and reviews from other travelers.

source: L'entreprise Couchsurfing a été fondée en janvier 2004 par le programmeur informatique Casey Fenton, qui avait trouvé un vol bon marché pour l'Islande, mais pas de point de chute pour y séjourner.
reference: Couchsurfing was founded in January 2004 after computer programmer Casey Fenton found a cheap flight to Iceland but did not have a place to stay.
translation: The company Couchsurfing was founded in January 2004 by the computer programmer Casey Fenton, who had found a cheap flight to Iceland but didn't have a place to stay.

source: Il a envoyé un e-mail aux étudiants de l'université locale et a reçu un nombre impressionnant d'offres d'hébergement gratuit.
reference: He emailed students at the local university and received an overwhelming number of offers for free accommodation.
translation: He sent an e-mail to students of the local university and received a number of free accommodation offers.

source: Les auberges s’adressent principalement aux jeunes – un client typique a une vingtaine d’années – mais on y trouve aussi souvent des voyageurs plus âgés.
reference: Hostels cater primarily to young people – a typical guest is in their twenties – but you can often find older travellers there too.
translation: The bars are mainly for young people - a typical client is between 20 and 30 years old - but they also often have older patrons.

source: Les familles avec enfants sont rares, mais certaines auberges les acceptent dans des chambres privées.
reference: Families with children are a rare sight, but some hostels do allow them in private rooms.
translation: Families with children are rare, but some hotels accept them in private rooms.

source: La ville de Pékin en Chine sera l'hôte des Jeux Olympiques d'hiver en 2022, ce qui en fera la première ville à avoir accueilli les Jeux d'été et ceux d'hiver.
reference: The city of Beijing in China will be the host city of the Olympic Winter Games in 2022, which will make it the first city to have hosted both the summer and winter Olympics.
translation: Beijing in China will host the Winter Olympics in 2022, which will be the first city to host the summer and winter Olympics.

source: Pékin accueillera les cérémonies d'ouverture et de clôture ainsi que les épreuves sur glace en salle.
reference: Beijing will host the opening and closing ceremonies and the indoor ice events.
translation: Beijing will host the opening and closing ceremonies and the ice skating events.

source: D'autres épreuves de ski se dérouleront dans la station de ski de Taizicheng à Zhangjiakou, à environ 220 km (140 pieds) de Pékin.
reference: Other skiing events will be at the Taizicheng ski area in Zhangjiakou, about 220 km (140 miles) from Beijing.
translation: Other ski races will take place in Taizicheng Ski Station in Zhangjiakou, about 220 km (140 feet) from Beijing.

source: La plupart des temples tiennent un festival annuel qui commence en fin novembre et se termine à la mi-mai, qui varie selon le calendrier annuel de chacun.
reference: Most of the temples do have an Annual festival starting from November end to Mid of May, which varies according to each temple's annual calendar.
translation: Most temples hold a festival that starts in November and ends in May, which varies according to the annual calendar of each temple.

source: La plupart des festivals du temple sont célébrés dans le cadre de l'anniversaire du temple, de la divinité qui le préside, ou à l'occasion de tout autre événement majeur associé au temple.
reference: Most of the temple festivals is celebrated as part of temple's anniversary or presiding deity's birthday or any other major event associated with the temple.
translation: Most festivals of the temple are celebrated in the context of the temple's birthday, the god who holds it, or in the context of any other major event associated with the temple.

source: Les festivals des temples du Kerala sont très intéressants à voir, avec de fréquentes processions d'éléphants décorés, l'orchestre du temple, et d'autres festivités.
reference: Kerala's temple festivals are very interesting to see, with regular procession of decorated elephants, temple orchestra and other festivities.
translation: Kerala festivals are very interesting to see, with frequent procession of elephants decorated, the orchestra of the temple, and other festivities.

source: Une exposition internationale (communément appelée exposition universelle ou tout simplement expo) est un grand festival international des arts et des sciences.
reference: A World's Fair (commonly called World Exposition, or simply Expo) is large international festival of arts and sciences.
translation: A major international exhibition is a large international art and science festival.

source: Les pays participants organisent des expositions artistiques et éducatives dans leurs pavillons nationaux pour mettre en lumière les problèmes mondiaux ou la culture et l'histoire de leur pays.
reference: Participating countries present artistic and educational displays in national pavilions to showcase world issues or their country's culture and history.
translation: The participants organize art and education events in their national pavilions to showcase the issues of their country or the culture and history of their country.

source: Les expositions horticoles internationales sont des événements spécialisés qui présentent des vitrines florales, des jardins botaniques et tout ce qui concerne les plantes.
reference: International Horticultural Expositions are specialised events which showcase floral displays, botanical gardens and anything else to do with plants.
translation: International Horticultural Expositions are specialised events that present floral displays, botanical gardens and everything related to plants.

source: Bien qu'elles puisent théoriquement avoir lieu tous les ans (à condition que ce soit dans des pays différents), dans la pratique, ce n'est pas le cas.
reference: Although in theory they can take place annually (so long as they are in different countries), in practice they are not.
translation: They do, however, theoretically have to be held annually (in countries that are different from each other), in practice, it is not the case.

source: Ces manifestations durent normalement entre trois et six mois et se déroulent sur des sites d’au moins 50 hectares.
reference: These events normally last anywhere between three and six months, and are held on sites no smaller than 50 hectares.
translation: These protests normally last between three and six months and take place on sites of at least 50 hectares.

source: Il existe de nombreux formats de films différents qui ont été utilisés au fil des ans. Le film standard 35 mm (négatif 36 par 24 mm) est de loin le plus courant.
reference: There are many different film formats that have been used over the years. Standard 35 mm film (36 by 24 mm negative) is much the commonest.
translation: There are many different formats of films that have been used over the years. The standard 35 mm film (negatively 36 by 24 mm) is the most common.

source: Il peut généralement être réapprovisionné assez facilement en cas d'épuisement et offre une résolution à peu près comparable à celle d'un reflex numérique actuel.
reference: It can usually be replenished fairly easily if you run out, and gives resolution roughly comparable to a current DSLR.
translation: It can usually be reused fairly easily in case of a shortage and offers a resolution comparable to that of a digital reflex camera.

source: Certaines caméras de moyen format utilisent un format de 6 par 6 cm, plus précisément un négatif de 56 par 56 mm.
reference: Some medium-format film cameras use a 6 by 6 cm format, more precisely a 56 by 56 mm negative.
translation: Some medium-format cameras use a 6 by 6 cm format, more precisely a 56 by 56 mm negative.

source: Cela donne une résolution presque quatre fois supérieure à celle d'un négatif de 35 mm (3136 mm2 contre 864).
reference: This gives resolution almost four times that of a 35 mm negative (3136 mm2 versus 864).
translation: This gives a resolution almost four times that of a negative of 35mm (3136mm2 against 864).

source: La faune et la flore sauvages sont des thèmes parmi les plus difficiles à capturer pour un photographe, et nécessitent une combinaison de chance, de patience, d'expérience et un bon équipement.
reference: Wildlife is among the most challenging motifs for a photographer, and needs a combination of good luck, patience, experience and good equipment.
translation: The flora and fauna of wild areas are among the most difficult to capture for a photographer, and require patience, experience, and a good camera.

source: La photographie de la vie sauvage est souvent considérée comme allant de soi, mais comme pour la photographie en général, une image vaut mille mots.
reference: Wildlife photography is often taken for granted, but like photography in general, a picture is worth a thousand words.
translation: Wildlife photography is often considered to be a necessity, but as for photography in general, a picture is worth a thousand words.

source: La photographie de la vie sauvage nécessite souvent un long téléobjectif. Toutefois, d'autres scènes comme une volée d'oiseaux ou une minuscule créature exigent l'utilisation d'autres objectifs.
reference: Wildlife photography often requires a long telephoto lens, though things like a flock of birds or a tiny creature need other lenses.
translation: Wildlife photography requires often a long telephoto lens. However, other scenes like a flock of birds or a tiny creature require other lenses.

source: De nombreux animaux exotiques sont difficiles à trouver, et les parcs ont parfois des règles relatives à la prise de photos à des fins commerciales.
reference: Many exotic animals are hard to find, and parks sometimes have rules about taking photographs for commercial purposes.
translation: Many exotic animals are difficult to find, and parks have sometimes rules regarding taking photos for commercial purposes.

source: Les animaux sauvages peuvent être timides ou agressifs. L'environnement peut être froid, chaud ou autrement hostile.
reference: Wild animals might either be shy or aggressive. The environment might be cold, hot, or otherwise hostile.
translation: Animals can be shy or aggressive. The environment can be cold, hot or otherwise hostile.

source: Le monde compte plus de 5000 langues différentes, dont une vingtaine avec 50 millions de locuteurs ou plus.
reference: The world has over 5,000 different languages, including more than twenty with 50 million or more speakers.
translation: The world has more than 5000 different languages, including a dozen with 50 million or more speakers.

source: Les mots écrits sont également souvent plus faciles à comprendre que les mots prononcés. C'est particulièrement vrai pour les adresses, qui sont souvent difficiles à prononcer de manière compréhensible.
reference: Written words are often easier to understand than spoken words, also. This is especially true of addresses, which are often difficult to pronounce intelligibly.
translation: The words written are also often easier to understand than the words spoken. This is especially true for addresses, which are often difficult to pronounce in a comprehensible way.

source: De nombreuses nations, dans leur ensemble, parlent couramment l'anglais, et dans bien d'autres pays, on peut s'attendre à en trouver une connaissance partielle, surtout chez les jeunes.
reference: Many entire nations are completely fluent in English, and in even more you can expect a limited knowledge - especially among younger people.
translation: Many nations, in their whole, speak English, and in many other countries, it is likely that you will find a knowledge of it, especially among the young.

source: Imaginez, si vous le voulez bien, un habitant de Manchester, un habitant de Boston, un Jamaïcain et un habitant de Sydney, assis autour d’une même table de restaurant à Toronto.
reference: Imagine, if you will, a Mancunian, Bostonian, Jamaican and Sydneysider sitting around a table having dinner at a restaurant in Toronto.
translation: Imagine, if you please, a Manchester, Boston, Jamaican, and Sydney resident sitting around a table at a restaurant in Toronto.

source: Ils se régalent les uns les autres d’histoires de leurs villes natales, racontées avec leurs accents prononcés et leur argot local.
reference: They're regaling each other with stories from their hometowns, told in their distinct accents and local argot.
translation: They are sharing stories of their native cities, told in their accents and local dialect.

source: Acheter de la nourriture dans les supermarchés est généralement le moyen le moins cher de se nourrir. Sans possibilité de cuisiner, les choix sont cependant limités aux aliments prêts à l'emploi.
reference: Buying food in supermarkets is usually the cheapest way to get fed. Without cooking opportunities, choices are however limited to ready-made food.
translation: Food shopping is usually the cheapest way to get food. Without cooking, the choices are limited to ready-made food.

source: Les supermarchés proposent de manière croissante une gamme plus variée de plats cuisinés. Certains fournissent même un four à micro-ondes ou d'autres moyens pour réchauffer la nourriture.
reference: Increasingly supermarkets are getting a more varied section of ready-made food. Some even provide a microwave oven or other means to heat food.
translation: Supermarkets are increasingly offering a variety of food options. Some offer a microwave oven or other means to heat food.

source: Dans certains pays ou types de lieux de vente, on trouve au moins un restaurant sur place, souvent assez informel et pratiquant des prix abordables.
reference: In some countries or types of stores there is at least one on-site restaurant, often a rather informal one with affordable prices.
translation: In some countries or types of stores, at least one restaurant is on the menu, often informal and offering reasonably priced prices.

source: Faites des copies de votre police d'assurance et des coordonnées de votre assureur et emportez-les avec vous.
reference: Make and carry copies of your policy and your insurer's contact details with you.
translation: Do copies of your insurance policy and your insurance carrier's contact information and bring them with you.

source: Ils doivent présenter l'adresse e-mail et les numéros de téléphone internationaux de l'assureur pour obtenir des conseils/autorisations et effectuer les demandes d'indemnisation.
reference: They need to show the insurer's e-mail address and international phone numbers for advice/authorizations and making claims.
translation: They must present the address and international phone numbers of the insurance company for advice/authorizations and request compensation and insurance claims.

source: Ayez à disposition une autre copie dans vos bagages et en ligne (e-mail adressé à vous-même avec pièce jointe, ou stocké dans le « cloud »).
reference: Have another copy in your luggage and online (e-mail to yourself with attachment, or stored in the "cloud").
translation: Have a copy of the document in your baggage and online (e-mail sent to yourself with a link, or stored in the "cloud").

source: Si vous voyagez avec un ordinateur portable ou une tablette, conservez une copie dans sa mémoire ou son disque (accessibles hors connexion).
reference: If traveling with a laptop or tablet, store a copy in its memory or disc (accessible without the internet).
translation: If you travel with a laptop or tablet, keep a copy of it in your memory or disc (accessible from the internet).

source: Donnez également des exemplaires de la réglementation et des contacts aux compagnons de voyage et aux parents ou amis à la maison qui sont prêts à vous aider.
reference: Also give policy/contact copies to traveling companions and relatives or friends back home willing to help.
translation: Also give copies of the regulations and contact information to the companions of travel and the parents or friends in the house who are willing to help.

source: Les élans ne sont pas de nature agressive, mais se défendront s’ils se sentent en danger.
reference: Moose (also known as elk) aren't inherently aggressive, but will defend themselves if they perceive a threat.
translation: Lions are not aggressive, but will defend themselves if they feel threatened.

source: Lorsque les gens ne considèrent pas les élans comme potentiellement dangereux, ils peuvent s'approcher de trop près et se mettre en péril.
reference: When people don't see moose as potentially dangerous, they may approach too closely and put themselves at risk.
translation: When people don't consider the elves as potentially dangerous, they can approach too close and get in danger.

source: Buvez des boissons alcoolisées avec modération. L'alcool a des effets différents sur chacun, et il est très important de connaître ses limites.
reference: Drink alcoholic drinks with moderation. Alcohol affects everyone differently, and knowing your limit is very important.
translation: Drink alcohol with moderation. Alcohol has different effects on each, and it's very important to know your limits.

source: Parmi les problèmes de santé possibles à long terme dus à l’alcoolisme, on peut citer les dégâts sur le foie, mais aussi la cécité et la mort. Le danger potentiel est accru en cas de consommation d’alcool fabriqué illégalement.
reference: Possible long term health events from excessive drinking can include liver damage and even blindness and death. The potential danger is increased when consuming illegally produced alcohol.
translation: Among the possible long-term health problems due to alcoholism, there are the effects on the liver, but also the blindness and death. The danger of consuming illegally produced alcohol is increased in the presence of a harmful substance.

source: Les spiritueux illicites peuvent contenir diverses impuretés dangereuses, y compris du méthanol, qui peut causer la cécité ou la mort, même à petites doses.
reference: Illegal spirits can contain various dangerous impurities including methanol, which can cause blindness or death even in small doses.
translation: Illegal spirits can contain dangerous impurities, including methanol, which can cause blindness or death even at very small doses.

source: Les lunettes de vue peuvent coûter moins cher à l’étranger, en particulier dans les pays à faible revenu dans lesquels le coût du travail est plus bas.
reference: Eyeglasses can be cheaper in a foreign country, especially in low-income countries where labour costs are lower.
translation: The glasses can cost less in foreign countries, especially in low-income countries where the cost of labor is lower.

source: Pensez à vous faire examiner les yeux à domicile, surtout si votre assurance le couvre, et à ramener l'ordonnance qui sera ensuite déposée ailleurs.
reference: Consider getting an eye exam at home, especially if insurance covers it, and bringing the prescription along to be filed elsewhere.
translation: Think about getting your eyes examined at home, especially if your insurance covers it, and bring the prescription to the office.

source: Les cadres de marque haut de gamme vendus dans de telles régions du monde peuvent présenter deux problèmes : certains peuvent être des contrefaçons, et les cadres véritablement importés peuvent être plus chers que dans votre pays.
reference: High-end brand-name frames available in such areas may have two problems; some may be knock-offs, and the real imported ones may be more expensive than at home.
translation: The quality of the frames in such regions of the world can be two problems: some can be fake, and imported frames can be more expensive than in your country.

source: Le café est l’une des marchandises les plus vendues au monde, et vous pouvez probablement en trouver de nombreux types dans votre région d’origine.
reference: Coffee is one of the world's most traded commodities, and you can probably find many types in your home region.
translation: Coffee is one of the most traded commodities in the world, and you can probably find many types in your region of origin.

source: Néanmoins, il existe de nombreuses façons de boire le café dans le monde entier qui valent la peine d'être expérimentées.
reference: Nevertheless, there are many distinctive ways of drinking coffee around the world that are worth experiencing.
translation: Nevertheless, there are many ways to enjoy coffee in the world that deserve to be tried out.

source: Le canyoning (ou canyonisme) consiste à se rendre en bas d’un canyon, qui est soit sec, soit plein d’eau.
reference: Canyoning (or: canyoneering) is about going in a bottom of a canyon, which is either dry or full of water.
translation: Canyoning (or canyoning) is the practice of going down a canyon, which is either dry or full of water.

source: Le canyoning combine des éléments de natation, d'escalade et de saut, mais nécessite relativement peu d'entraînement ou de forme physique pour débuter, par rapport à, par exemple,  l'escalade, la plongée sous-marine ou le ski alpin.
reference: Canyoning combines elements from swimming, climbing and jumping--but requires relatively little training or physical shape to get started (compared to rock climbing, scuba diving or alpine skiing, for example).
translation: Canyoning combines elements of swimming, climbing, and jumping, but requires little or no physical training or form to begin, compared to, for example, swimming, jumping, or skiing.

source: La randonnée est une activité de plein air qui consiste à marcher dans des environnements naturels, souvent sur des sentiers de randonnée.
reference: Hiking is an outdoor activity which consists of walking in natural environments, often on hiking trails.
translation: The hiking is a type of outdoor activity that consists of walking in natural environments, often on hiking trails.

source: Une randonnée d'une journée implique des distances de moins d'un mile jusqu'à des distances plus longues pouvant être parcourues en un seul jour.
reference: Day hiking involves distances of less than a mile up to longer distances that can be covered in a single day.
translation: A day hike involves distances of less than a mile to longer distances that can be covered in one day.

source: Pour une randonnée d'une journée sur un sentier peu difficile, il suffit de quelques préparatifs et toute personne relativement en bonne santé peut en profiter.
reference: For a day hike along an easy trail little preparations are needed, and any moderately fit person can enjoy them.
translation: For a day hike on a relatively easy trail, just a few preparations and anyone with a good sense of fitness can enjoy it.

source: Les familles ayant de jeunes enfants peuvent avoir besoin de plus de préparation, mais il est possible de passer une journée en plein air, même avec des bébés et des enfants d’âge préscolaire.
reference: Families with small children may need more preparations, but a day outdoors is easily possible even with babies and pre-school children.
translation: Families with young children can need more preparation, but it is possible to spend a day in the wild, even with babies and children of pre-school age.

source: Sur le plan international, il existe près de 200 organisations de visite en course à pied. La plupart d’entre elles fonctionnent indépendamment.
reference: Internationally, there are nearly 200 running tour organizations. Most of them operate independently.
translation: Internationally, there are nearly 200 organizations that run races in the distance. Most of them operate independently.

source: Le successeur de Global Running Tours, Go Running Tours, met en réseau des dizaines de prestataires de services de jogging touristique sur quatre continents.
reference: The Global Running Tours successor, Go Running Tours networks dozens of sightrunning providers on four continents.
translation: Global Running Tours, Go Running Tours, is a touring company that connects hundreds of travel agents in four continents.

source: Ayant ses racines dans le Running Tours Barcelona de Barcelone et le Running Copenhagen de Copenhague, elle a rapidement été rejointe par le Running Tours Prague basé à Prague et d'autres.
reference: With roots in Barcelona's Running Tours Barcelona and Copenhagen's Running Copenhagen, it was quickly joined by Running Tours Prague based in Prague and others.
translation: She has roots in the Running Tours Barcelona in Barcelona and the Running Copenhagen in Copenhagen, and has quickly been joined by the Running Tours Prague based in Prague and other.
